1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:03,436
- Last week, there were eliminations.
- Right.

2
00:00:03,659 --> 00:00:06,749
(Revealing the Eliminated Participants:
Yoon Jung-woo & Yang Ji-min)

3
00:00:07,029 --> 00:00:09,014
Unfortunately, two
participants were eliminated.

4
00:00:09,039 --> 00:00:13,358
So I'm worried that some
of us here might get eliminated, too.

5
00:00:13,533 --> 00:00:16,258
I always come to film
with an uneasy heart.

6
00:00:16,593 --> 00:00:17,824
You're so funny.

7
00:00:18,026 --> 00:00:21,099
The two people who came to find
true love happened to get eliminated.

8
00:00:21,124 --> 00:00:22,124
Right.

9
00:00:22,149 --> 00:00:25,006
Now the couples are in a disarray.

10
00:00:25,031 --> 00:00:28,480
In-seong and Jung-woo
were in a sweet relationship,

11
00:00:28,505 --> 00:00:31,289
and they were building
up their affection.

12
00:00:31,314 --> 00:00:34,032
But Jung-woo was eliminated,
and now, In-seong is alone.

13
00:00:34,057 --> 00:00:35,335
She cried a lot.

14
00:00:35,738 --> 00:00:37,600
As for the Ji-min and Ji-min couple,

15
00:00:37,625 --> 00:00:41,271
Yang Ji-min finally mustered
up the courage to get close

16
00:00:41,296 --> 00:00:46,052
to Ahn Ji-min, but she
ended up getting eliminated.

17
00:00:46,220 --> 00:00:50,564
I'm so curious what choices the
other participants will make next.

18
00:00:50,589 --> 00:00:54,497
You know that spoiler
clip we saw in episode 1?

19
00:00:54,798 --> 00:00:56,342
That will unfold in tonight's episode.

20
00:00:56,367 --> 00:00:57,858
"You were selfish, Su-won."

21
00:00:57,883 --> 00:00:59,988
- Yeah. That clip with the wine bottle.
- Right?

22
00:01:01,379 --> 00:01:03,427
- That's tonight?
- That's tonight.

23
00:01:04,477 --> 00:01:07,026
- We'll be able to find out what happened.
- Oh my goodness.

24
00:01:07,966 --> 00:01:09,347
Shall we check out the video?

25
00:01:10,413 --> 00:01:13,407
(The stormy night when the eliminated
participants left has passed by.)

26
00:01:14,179 --> 00:01:17,125
(Contrary to how the others
feel, it's a peaceful day.)

27
00:01:17,150 --> 00:01:19,428
Gosh, the weather is
nice like nothing happened.

28
00:01:19,453 --> 00:01:22,042
(The morning of the sixth day)

29
00:01:22,804 --> 00:01:25,459
(Everyone is asleep as usual.)

30
00:01:26,116 --> 00:01:28,773
(The only difference is
that one bed is empty.)

31
00:01:29,577 --> 00:01:32,720
(Ji-min had fallen asleep
in Jung-woo's bed.)

32
00:01:33,595 --> 00:01:35,231
(Jolt)

33
00:01:39,570 --> 00:01:41,387
(Disheveled)

34
00:01:42,042 --> 00:01:43,495
Wow, Won-jae.

35
00:01:44,981 --> 00:01:46,251
He has a nice body.

36
00:01:48,785 --> 00:01:52,566
(They haven't gotten used
to Jung-woo's absence yet.)

37
00:01:52,591 --> 00:01:53,831
They have a lot on their mind.

38
00:01:53,856 --> 00:01:56,119
It's only morning, but
there's a lot on their mind.

39
00:01:56,144 --> 00:01:59,677
- Let's run away.
- Jung-woo...

40
00:02:01,095 --> 00:02:03,119
Goodness.

41
00:02:03,144 --> 00:02:05,763
(Jung-woo's elimination makes
In-seong feel the emptiest.)

42
00:02:08,022 --> 00:02:09,649
He's really not here anymore.

43
00:02:10,422 --> 00:02:12,613
Is there someone else
you talked a lot with?

44
00:02:13,401 --> 00:02:15,560
There's Ji-min, but...

45
00:02:16,369 --> 00:02:18,888
Honestly, there wasn't
really anyone but Jung-woo.

46
00:02:18,913 --> 00:02:21,224
- Oh no.
- That's right.

47
00:02:22,459 --> 00:02:24,030
I don't know what to do.

48
00:02:25,454 --> 00:02:28,089
- Is there really no one?
- No one?

49
00:02:29,260 --> 00:02:32,371
I did have fun with Ji-min,

50
00:02:32,924 --> 00:02:35,185
but he might think...

51
00:02:35,210 --> 00:02:39,266
- "Is she coming to me now
'cause Jung-woo's gone?" - No way.

52
00:02:39,291 --> 00:02:42,063
- That's definitely not the case.
- But it's not false either.

53
00:02:42,088 --> 00:02:43,827
- It's not like that at all.
- Really?

54
00:02:43,852 --> 00:02:46,535
Yeah. It's not like you
guys were officially going out.

55
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:49,355
- Right.
- We're all just here to meet people.

56
00:02:49,380 --> 00:02:51,517
Try talking with Ji-min again.

57
00:02:52,409 --> 00:02:54,441
- Should I?
- Try talking to him.

58
00:02:55,413 --> 00:02:56,961
No one thinks that way.

59
00:02:56,986 --> 00:02:58,186
- Really?
- Yeah.

60
00:02:58,893 --> 00:03:00,639
What will happen to In-seong now?

61
00:03:00,664 --> 00:03:04,245
If In-seong is truly a Love Catcher
and Jung-woo is the only one she sees,

62
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:09,073
then I think she'd think about
why she's at the Love Mansion.

63
00:03:10,336 --> 00:03:15,364
(Is there someone who
will fill their emptiness?)

64
00:03:17,291 --> 00:03:18,664
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes.

65
00:03:18,689 --> 00:03:21,080
- Your eyes aren't swollen.
- Right? I wonder why.

66
00:03:21,105 --> 00:03:22,509
My eyes are swollen.

67
00:03:23,917 --> 00:03:24,917
You surprised me.

68
00:03:25,166 --> 00:03:26,800
Good morning, Su-won.

69
00:03:28,863 --> 00:03:31,097
(In-seong leaves
without saying anything.)

70
00:03:32,245 --> 00:03:33,245
Goodness.

71
00:03:33,270 --> 00:03:36,110
He doesn't need help with the dishes?

72
00:03:37,512 --> 00:03:39,615
- Da-Na keeps helping her.
- Yeah.

73
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:42,688
(It's not easy to approach someone new.)

74
00:03:44,625 --> 00:03:47,782
(Su-won and Ha-neul are awkward as usual.)

75
00:03:48,252 --> 00:03:49,252
(Glance)

76
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:54,210
- So what's going to happen?
- What is she holding against her head?

77
00:03:56,252 --> 00:03:59,842
As times goes on, the conflict is getting
deeper because they're not talking it out.

78
00:03:59,867 --> 00:04:02,957
- In the end, he couldn't talk
to her yesterday. - Yeah.

79
00:04:02,982 --> 00:04:04,912
This keeps repeating.

80
00:04:09,758 --> 00:04:10,821
(Glance)

81
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:13,437
- Why do you have that on your head?
- Huh?

82
00:04:13,462 --> 00:04:16,093
- Why do you have that...?
- I bumped it hard against something.

83
00:04:16,345 --> 00:04:19,577
- Where?
- The light next to the dressing table.

84
00:04:20,210 --> 00:04:21,771
(This morning)

85
00:04:22,210 --> 00:04:26,123
(Ha-neul bumped her
head with a loud noise.)

86
00:04:26,557 --> 00:04:27,557
Oh no.

87
00:04:27,582 --> 00:04:29,826
(They talk awkwardly
while looking elsewhere.)

88
00:04:30,156 --> 00:04:31,958
Goodness, what do we do?

89
00:04:31,983 --> 00:04:34,689
(The things he want to say
keep getting stuck in their throat.)

90
00:04:35,756 --> 00:04:38,026
I want to go out for a date.

91
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:41,102
Did you already vote?

92
00:04:41,127 --> 00:04:43,810
- I have to do it.
- Oh, me, too.

93
00:04:44,509 --> 00:04:45,509
I don't know.

94
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:47,567
I have no idea.

95
00:04:47,592 --> 00:04:51,192
(Ha-neul turns a blind eye,
and Su-won is frustrated.)

96
00:04:56,412 --> 00:04:58,486
Gosh, the weather is so nice, but...

97
00:05:05,288 --> 00:05:07,923
(Ji-min goes outside
with a heavy expression.)

98
00:05:07,948 --> 00:05:10,226
- No way.
- He's not following her, is he?

99
00:05:10,251 --> 00:05:12,063
I think he is.

100
00:05:14,233 --> 00:05:16,098
Did you decide what you're gonna do?

101
00:05:18,215 --> 00:05:20,786
You have to make your final choice later.

102
00:05:20,811 --> 00:05:22,566
Yeah. I'm not gonna choose anyone.

103
00:05:24,841 --> 00:05:27,452
He finally knew how Ji-min
left, but she's gone now.

104
00:05:31,030 --> 00:05:32,562
You must be upset that Ji-min's gone.

105
00:05:35,249 --> 00:05:37,849
There's a mistake that guys make a lot.

106
00:05:38,125 --> 00:05:40,586
- You don't notice them when
they're around... - Exactly!

107
00:05:40,611 --> 00:05:43,610
- But you notice them when they're gone.
- You can't take them for granted.

108
00:05:43,635 --> 00:05:45,082
You fools!

109
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:49,809
- Where are you guys going?
- I'm going to the room.

110
00:05:49,834 --> 00:05:50,954
- Really?
- Yeah.

111
00:05:52,443 --> 00:05:54,110
I'm gonna go to the room.

112
00:05:57,422 --> 00:05:58,489
Did he see them?

113
00:05:58,514 --> 00:06:01,089
- He saw them, right?
- Yeah.

114
00:06:01,725 --> 00:06:03,720
- They have to talk now.
- Right.

115
00:06:06,768 --> 00:06:10,441
(Su-won and Ha-neul have gotten more
awkward ever since "Men's Invitation.")

116
00:06:12,239 --> 00:06:16,947
(Could they go to back to
those days when they first met?)

117
00:06:16,972 --> 00:06:20,611
It's unfortunate because
she once told him

118
00:06:20,636 --> 00:06:23,764
to get to know other people.

119
00:06:23,789 --> 00:06:26,514
So I wonder if that's
why he went on a date with Da-Na.

120
00:06:26,539 --> 00:06:29,754
Women's language is a bit
difficult. Judging from how much

121
00:06:29,779 --> 00:06:33,266
she's struggling right now, that's
probably not what she meant.

122
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:36,921
- Whatever it is, they have to talk it out.
- Right.

123
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:42,925
We know how Ha-neul
feels, but Su-won has no idea.

124
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:43,950
Yeah.

125
00:06:45,414 --> 00:06:46,787
(Glance)

126
00:06:50,312 --> 00:06:52,574
- Isn't there anything?
- Is he looking for medicine?

127
00:06:53,558 --> 00:06:57,658
(After searching for a long
time, he takes a mask and pen.)

128
00:06:58,387 --> 00:06:59,920
Should I write it here?

129
00:07:01,374 --> 00:07:04,975
(What is he trying to do
with the mask and pen?)

130
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,597
- Today...
- Huh? A letter?

131
00:07:12,222 --> 00:07:15,876
(He starts to write something on
the mask as if he's made up his mind.)

132
00:07:17,599 --> 00:07:19,229
(Sincere)

133
00:07:20,209 --> 00:07:22,962
(After looking and looking,
he puts the cap back on.)

134
00:07:25,007 --> 00:07:27,206
(What did he write down?)

135
00:07:27,231 --> 00:07:28,231
I'm curious.

136
00:07:32,256 --> 00:07:35,529
(A cute mask letter filled with his heart.)

137
00:07:36,447 --> 00:07:39,425
- What does it say? - "The weather
is nice and the sky is pretty."

138
00:07:39,450 --> 00:07:41,347
"How about we go for a walk and talk?"

139
00:07:41,985 --> 00:07:45,040
- He decorated the word "sky."
- What?

140
00:07:45,734 --> 00:07:47,468
That's an adorable letter!

141
00:07:48,334 --> 00:07:52,170
I wanted to write something and
give it to her, but there was no paper.

142
00:07:52,498 --> 00:07:57,403
I looked for anything in
the room and saw a mask.

143
00:07:57,428 --> 00:08:01,367
I wrote something on
there, asking her to talk.

144
00:08:02,571 --> 00:08:08,922
I did a word play with the word "Ha-neul."

145
00:08:09,427 --> 00:08:11,507
- He finally mustered up the courage.
- Yup.

146
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:16,303
(His way of expressing himself
in order to change her heart.)

147
00:08:17,958 --> 00:08:21,255
(Will he be able to deliver the letter?)

148
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:24,876
(Jae-hyung and In-seong
are talking with Ha-neul.)

149
00:08:25,714 --> 00:08:28,142
It doesn't seem like a good timing either.

150
00:08:30,605 --> 00:08:32,130
(He just passes by?)

151
00:08:32,155 --> 00:08:33,155
Again?

152
00:08:34,294 --> 00:08:37,415
- Hurry up and give it to her!
- This is what I was afraid of.

153
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:42,624
I think Su-won has a hard time approaching
her when there's a lot of people.

154
00:08:42,649 --> 00:08:43,938
- That's his personality.
- Yeah.

155
00:08:43,963 --> 00:08:45,422
Gosh, it's unfortunate.

156
00:08:46,611 --> 00:08:48,442
(Trudge)

157
00:08:49,795 --> 00:08:50,795
What do I do?

158
00:08:53,798 --> 00:08:57,119
But I understand him. I don't think
I'd be able to give it to her either.

159
00:08:57,797 --> 00:09:00,272
(He doesn't have much time to hesitate.)

160
00:09:02,657 --> 00:09:04,371
He's mustering up the courage again.

161
00:09:05,208 --> 00:09:06,533
He's trying again. Way to go!

162
00:09:08,776 --> 00:09:09,776
(Glance)

163
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,428
You'll get COVID-19.
Wear a mask.

164
00:09:15,773 --> 00:09:18,102
He told her to wear a mask
because she'll get COVID-19!

165
00:09:18,317 --> 00:09:19,936
But what about those two?

166
00:09:20,723 --> 00:09:24,765
We follow all the COVID-19
guidelines while filming.

167
00:09:26,016 --> 00:09:28,413
- That was cute!
- That's really Su-won-like.

168
00:09:28,948 --> 00:09:30,543
You'll get COVID-19.
Wear a mask.

169
00:09:34,085 --> 00:09:36,462
(He seems indifferent, but
he had taken a huge step.)

170
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:39,083
She saw it.

171
00:09:41,413 --> 00:09:42,413
Finally.

172
00:09:42,438 --> 00:09:44,589
Okay, you're definitely
not gonna get COVID-19.

173
00:09:44,614 --> 00:09:46,956
- Yeah. I'll never get it.
- That's good.

174
00:09:48,736 --> 00:09:52,477
(His entire body is twisting
up out of embarrassment.)

175
00:09:54,371 --> 00:09:56,108
(Embarrassed)

176
00:09:57,511 --> 00:10:02,136
(Did Su-won's heart reach Ha-neul?)

177
00:10:02,957 --> 00:10:05,824
Did she read his heart?

178
00:10:06,375 --> 00:10:08,677
(Uneasy)

179
00:10:13,463 --> 00:10:15,152
Why'd you get here so late?

180
00:10:15,177 --> 00:10:17,862
I was talking with them.

181
00:10:18,524 --> 00:10:20,501
- You were waiting for me?
- Huh?

182
00:10:20,526 --> 00:10:21,913
You were waiting for me?

183
00:10:22,174 --> 00:10:24,043
I thought other people were in there.

184
00:10:24,068 --> 00:10:25,535
I was waiting for you.

185
00:10:26,812 --> 00:10:28,012
They're going out.

186
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:30,652
- The weather is nice, too.
- What will they talk about?

187
00:10:30,823 --> 00:10:34,235
- The weather is nice.
- It's a nice day.

188
00:10:38,974 --> 00:10:42,776
Were you upset because
of my decision yesterday?

189
00:10:43,717 --> 00:10:45,241
No, I expected it.

190
00:10:47,015 --> 00:10:49,443
I had no idea you wouldn't
get asked out on a date.

191
00:10:49,928 --> 00:10:51,707
I knew very well I wouldn't get picked.

192
00:10:55,373 --> 00:10:58,460
I assumed Ji-min would ask you.

193
00:10:58,965 --> 00:11:01,004
Does it look like there's
something between us?

194
00:11:02,087 --> 00:11:03,317
I don't know what to say.

195
00:11:04,189 --> 00:11:05,855
- Did you have a good time?
- Huh?

196
00:11:06,476 --> 00:11:07,604
It was just...

197
00:11:08,252 --> 00:11:13,379
It could seem a bit selfish,

198
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:17,313
but after talking with Da-Na, I thought,

199
00:11:18,731 --> 00:11:21,825
"It's just this much."

200
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:25,600
So I just wanted to tell you how I felt.

201
00:11:27,011 --> 00:11:32,796
You might not be curious,
but just in case you are.

202
00:11:33,524 --> 00:11:35,436
She's still kind of upset.

203
00:11:36,551 --> 00:11:38,085
No matter what I say...

204
00:11:39,514 --> 00:11:41,114
No, I'm really okay now.

205
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:45,121
Yesterday, I felt a bit strange
when I heard you call Da-Na...

206
00:11:46,785 --> 00:11:52,088
It was the first time you came over and
called her, and everyone looked at me.

207
00:11:52,113 --> 00:11:54,265
I was a bit...

208
00:11:55,442 --> 00:11:58,042
Da-Na, can you come out here for a sec?

209
00:12:00,059 --> 00:12:04,330
(When Su-won asked for Da-Na,
all the girls glanced at Ha-neul.)

210
00:12:04,764 --> 00:12:09,248
I had a really hard
time on that day we talked.

211
00:12:09,706 --> 00:12:11,452
But starting from yesterday...

212
00:12:11,477 --> 00:12:13,477
These aren't just empty words.

213
00:12:14,329 --> 00:12:15,329
I'm okay.

214
00:12:16,401 --> 00:12:17,672
You don't have to feel sorry.

215
00:12:18,652 --> 00:12:20,819
I had a good time yesterday.

216
00:12:21,723 --> 00:12:23,453
So you don't have to worry.

217
00:12:23,943 --> 00:12:25,855
Aren't those words scarier?

218
00:12:26,303 --> 00:12:29,906
If I hadn't actively pursued you...

219
00:12:30,863 --> 00:12:34,593
I'm not good at approaching people first.

220
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:39,828
So I do like guys who
actively approach me.

221
00:12:40,453 --> 00:12:44,304
But while hanging out
with you, I realized that

222
00:12:44,329 --> 00:12:47,044
I don't have to get to
know the other guys.

223
00:12:47,548 --> 00:12:51,087
But despite the fact that you
spent a lot of time with me,

224
00:12:52,679 --> 00:12:55,163
you suddenly said you wanted
to get to know someone else.

225
00:12:57,168 --> 00:12:58,652
So I was a bit...

226
00:13:02,055 --> 00:13:05,221
(Due to the overwhelming
sadness, she can't say anything.)

227
00:13:05,246 --> 00:13:08,216
- Su-won knows how she feels
for the first time. - Yeah.

228
00:13:09,904 --> 00:13:12,261
- Why are they always offbeat?
- I know.

229
00:13:13,182 --> 00:13:17,821
(Will they be able to straighten the
wrong timing and twisted hearts?)

230
00:13:18,739 --> 00:13:21,223
(Just then, Ji-min
appears in front of them.)

231
00:13:21,524 --> 00:13:22,643
(Glance)

232
00:13:24,604 --> 00:13:27,759
(Is it for their sake? He
ignores them and goes inside.)

233
00:13:29,532 --> 00:13:32,639
(Ji-min enters the room by himself.)

234
00:13:36,689 --> 00:13:40,036
(He sighs deeply as if
he has a lot on his mind...)

235
00:13:42,192 --> 00:13:45,392
Isn't there someone new
you want to get to know?

236
00:13:46,848 --> 00:13:47,848
I don't know.

237
00:13:48,031 --> 00:13:51,182
You're not looking at other guys.
You're not interested in them.

238
00:13:51,207 --> 00:13:53,455
You're really not good at
approaching people, huh?

239
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,990
Yeah, I can never do that!

240
00:13:56,055 --> 00:13:57,776
- I'm curious about him.
- Me?

241
00:13:57,995 --> 00:14:01,066
So you don't think Da-na's the one?

242
00:14:01,586 --> 00:14:05,046
After talking with
her, I became certain.

243
00:14:05,295 --> 00:14:08,105
- That it's Ha-neul?
- Yup.

244
00:14:10,596 --> 00:14:17,016
Ji-min knows that Ha-neul
and Su-won like each other.

245
00:14:17,041 --> 00:14:20,691
(He knows how they feel,
so his mind is complicated.)

246
00:14:24,057 --> 00:14:27,005
(A long time later...
Ji-min heads somewhere.)

247
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:28,030
Where is he going?

248
00:14:28,202 --> 00:14:31,407
(Who will Ji-min's heart go to now?)

249
00:14:32,563 --> 00:14:33,563
Da-Na?

250
00:14:35,216 --> 00:14:37,255
- Are you sleeping?
- He's going to Da-Na?

251
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:39,773
- Wanna talk?
- Huh? Sure.

252
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:42,143
What are you doing here?

253
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:46,128
Just. I feel restless.

254
00:14:46,153 --> 00:14:47,671
- Why?
- I'm not sure.

255
00:14:48,205 --> 00:14:51,118
Then again, Da-Na kind of liked Jung-woo.

256
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:52,732
- That's true.
- Yeah.

257
00:14:52,757 --> 00:14:54,208
But he left.

258
00:14:55,715 --> 00:14:59,555
- How are you?
- I'm... restless, too.

259
00:14:59,580 --> 00:15:00,580
Yeah.

260
00:15:01,856 --> 00:15:03,589
Did you make up your mind?

261
00:15:04,110 --> 00:15:06,665
- I think so.
- Really?

262
00:15:06,690 --> 00:15:08,256
Yeah, I think so.

263
00:15:10,015 --> 00:15:13,642
There's only one day
left until the final day.

264
00:15:16,204 --> 00:15:18,704
- I was honestly curious about you.
- Oh, really?

265
00:15:19,159 --> 00:15:21,072
So I wanted to get to know you.

266
00:15:21,097 --> 00:15:24,646
- We've never talked along before.
- Right.

267
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:28,848
I don't know what your personality is like,
what you like, or what's your ideal type.

268
00:15:31,022 --> 00:15:34,172
- What kind of person are you?
- Me?

269
00:15:34,779 --> 00:15:36,478
What kind of person do you think I am?

270
00:15:36,503 --> 00:15:37,503
- You?
- Yeah.

271
00:15:37,838 --> 00:15:39,108
You're really...

272
00:15:40,012 --> 00:15:42,769
How do I put it? You're refreshing?
That's what you seem like.

273
00:15:42,794 --> 00:15:46,200
You seem to do things
without hesitation here.

274
00:15:46,225 --> 00:15:48,648
- That's not good.
- No, it's a good thing.

275
00:15:49,096 --> 00:15:53,017
I can't really lie, and I'm not good
at hiding my facial expressions.

276
00:15:54,125 --> 00:15:57,466
So it's obvious if I'm happy, and
it's obvious if I don't like something.

277
00:15:58,098 --> 00:15:59,985
Right. I saw everything.

278
00:16:00,010 --> 00:16:03,012
I'm transparent. And I'm easy to control.

279
00:16:03,521 --> 00:16:06,023
That's the biggest lie that
Money Catchers make.

280
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:08,463
"I can't hide my
expressions. I'm bad at lying."

281
00:16:09,657 --> 00:16:10,990
You're a Money Catcher!

282
00:16:13,272 --> 00:16:14,472
I have a question.

283
00:16:15,183 --> 00:16:17,791
How many people are you interested in here?

284
00:16:18,116 --> 00:16:19,116
Interested?

285
00:16:19,777 --> 00:16:22,150
As of right now, just one person.

286
00:16:22,175 --> 00:16:24,130
- One person?
- Yes. For now.

287
00:16:24,155 --> 00:16:25,586
- I see.
- One person?

288
00:16:25,974 --> 00:16:27,093
Is it Won-jae?

289
00:16:27,303 --> 00:16:31,875
On the day we did the jazz
dance, you looked really charming.

290
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:33,886
- Really?
- Honestly, my heart fluttered then.

291
00:16:33,911 --> 00:16:34,911
When?

292
00:16:36,422 --> 00:16:40,250
(Their partners weren't there,
so they practiced together.)

293
00:16:40,682 --> 00:16:41,912
You're good!

294
00:16:43,055 --> 00:16:44,985
- Really?
- My heart fluttered then.

295
00:16:45,010 --> 00:16:48,107
- Really?
- Yeah. I had a mini heart attack.

296
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:49,912
- Really? - Yeah, it was charming.

297
00:16:52,012 --> 00:16:56,291
He seems to be in a bit of a rush, so it
makes me think he's a Money Catcher.

298
00:16:56,548 --> 00:17:00,101
It's very ambiguous because
Yang Ji-min, who obviously

299
00:17:00,126 --> 00:17:03,226
expressed her interest
in him, left the mansion.

300
00:17:03,461 --> 00:17:05,976
But then he talked with Ha-neul a lot.

301
00:17:06,186 --> 00:17:09,099
So if he suddenly tells Da-Na
that his heart fluttered for her...

302
00:17:09,124 --> 00:17:11,355
- She'll be flustered.
- I think it'll be complicated.

303
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:13,111
I think I know what's going on.

304
00:17:13,136 --> 00:17:14,279
- What?
- Is there a reason?

305
00:17:14,304 --> 00:17:19,251
Ji-min was interested in
Da-Na in the beginning,

306
00:17:19,276 --> 00:17:22,195
but she was too popular, and
when he was starting to like

307
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:25,138
her more and more and finally
about to express his liking,

308
00:17:25,523 --> 00:17:30,118
Yang Ji-min appeared out of the blue.

309
00:17:30,143 --> 00:17:33,925
- That's possible.
- So he kind of hesitated then.

310
00:17:34,270 --> 00:17:36,087
- That makes sense, too.
- Right?

311
00:17:36,112 --> 00:17:40,670
After thinking for a long time, he finally
made up his mind and went to talk to Da-Na.

312
00:17:40,695 --> 00:17:42,007
That's possible.

313
00:17:43,694 --> 00:17:46,558
Did it go well?
Did you have a good talk with Da-Na?

314
00:17:46,583 --> 00:17:50,395
Yes. It went better than I expected.

315
00:17:50,589 --> 00:17:52,454
- I see.
- What?

316
00:17:52,981 --> 00:17:56,711
I talked to Da-Na, and it was
different from what I've heard about her.

317
00:17:56,736 --> 00:17:57,736
I see.

318
00:17:59,646 --> 00:18:01,112
Oh, something came up.

319
00:18:06,591 --> 00:18:07,591
What?

320
00:18:07,733 --> 00:18:09,000
Is it an interview?

321
00:18:12,117 --> 00:18:14,984
- What's going on?
- Is it live?

322
00:18:16,489 --> 00:18:19,036
- Why is everyone surprised?
- What's going on?

323
00:18:20,065 --> 00:18:21,858
Hang on. Is that here?

324
00:18:22,289 --> 00:18:23,717
Something's up.

325
00:18:28,512 --> 00:18:32,225
(Eliminated Ji-min suddenly
appears on the screen.)

326
00:18:33,658 --> 00:18:35,649
- No! I can't believe this!

327
00:18:36,001 --> 00:18:37,001
Really?

328
00:18:37,026 --> 00:18:39,756
(At her appearance,
the girls grow teary first.)

329
00:18:40,999 --> 00:18:45,380
- No one expected this.
- My heart really breaks for her.

330
00:18:46,209 --> 00:18:48,902
(With her unexpected appearance,
the guys grow nervous...)

331
00:18:48,927 --> 00:18:51,809
(What did Ji-min have to say?)

332
00:18:52,304 --> 00:18:55,121
I have no idea why I was eliminated.

333
00:18:56,450 --> 00:18:57,850
We don't know either!

334
00:18:59,782 --> 00:19:02,361
I have no idea why I was eliminated.

335
00:19:02,386 --> 00:19:05,627
I've never really done
anything suspicious in front

336
00:19:05,652 --> 00:19:09,016
of the guys for them to
suspect me as a Money Catcher.

337
00:19:09,609 --> 00:19:13,867
Some guys just chose me because
they didn't want the girl they want

338
00:19:13,892 --> 00:19:17,898
to get eliminated so they just
chose me because I'm the easiest.

339
00:19:18,929 --> 00:19:23,302
Who do you think is a Money Catcher?

340
00:19:25,046 --> 00:19:26,046
Oh my god!

341
00:19:28,191 --> 00:19:30,318
No way.
No way.

342
00:19:31,354 --> 00:19:34,687
- Wow, she's coming out strong.
- I'm so nervous.

343
00:19:35,867 --> 00:19:38,867
I talked with the girls
a lot, and the one I

344
00:19:39,328 --> 00:19:42,250
suspect the most to be a
Money Catcher is Yeo-min.

345
00:19:44,628 --> 00:19:46,136
(You don't say...)

346
00:19:47,540 --> 00:19:49,927
(The men can't help
but keenly listen.)

347
00:19:49,952 --> 00:19:54,042
From the beginning,
she was actively chatting

348
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:58,512
with the guys and trying
to go on dates with them.

349
00:19:59,097 --> 00:20:00,239
Really? Me?

350
00:20:03,475 --> 00:20:05,626
Hmm, I was kind of suspicious about that.

351
00:20:06,042 --> 00:20:08,907
As for the guys...

352
00:20:12,041 --> 00:20:16,127
I think Su-won and
Jae-hyung are Money Catchers.

353
00:20:16,372 --> 00:20:17,473
(In disbelief)

354
00:20:17,728 --> 00:20:19,561
I thought you were a Love Catcher!

355
00:20:19,794 --> 00:20:23,358
I think Su-won and
Jae-hyung are Money Catchers.

356
00:20:25,269 --> 00:20:31,643
From the beginning, it was obvious
that he was actively pursuing Ha-neul.

357
00:20:33,792 --> 00:20:37,528
I'm not... but people
keep seeing me that way.

358
00:20:38,406 --> 00:20:45,321
And Jae-hyung was so generously nice to me
that it made me think he's a Money Catcher.

359
00:20:46,167 --> 00:20:48,621
- Oh no. - She's suspecting me
even though I'm nice to her.

360
00:20:48,646 --> 00:20:50,169
I honestly liked her.

361
00:20:50,532 --> 00:20:52,467
(They can't hold
back their laughter.)

362
00:20:52,903 --> 00:20:57,231
- Why is he so funny?
- He's just originally excessive.

363
00:20:57,951 --> 00:20:58,951
Ji-min.

364
00:21:00,652 --> 00:21:04,518
I'm a Love Catcher and the
other girls are Money Catchers.

365
00:21:04,543 --> 00:21:10,586
Ever since the beginning, I kept
saying that I liked you in the interviews.

366
00:21:10,611 --> 00:21:13,194
- Wow, she's not holding back.
- Seriously.

367
00:21:13,777 --> 00:21:19,659
But you kept uselessly going after
Ha-neul and In-seong. I'm very upset.

368
00:21:19,894 --> 00:21:24,560
It's too bad that I was eliminated,
but you'll regret not noticing me.

369
00:21:25,152 --> 00:21:27,089
She's saying everything on her mind.

370
00:21:27,445 --> 00:21:31,212
(Her message was so
honest that his legs gave out.)

371
00:21:31,796 --> 00:21:33,716
She knows it was useless.

372
00:21:34,226 --> 00:21:37,148
Just because she's young
doesn't mean she's tactless.

373
00:21:37,777 --> 00:21:40,412
She's very keen compared to her age.

374
00:21:41,830 --> 00:21:43,218
Wow, great job.

375
00:21:44,379 --> 00:21:46,681
- Jung-woo!
- Jung-woo!

376
00:21:47,685 --> 00:21:48,952
Out of the guys....

377
00:21:50,208 --> 00:21:53,124
I kind of think Won-jae is one.

378
00:21:55,112 --> 00:21:56,294
Really?

379
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:59,760
And I think Da-Na is one, too.

380
00:22:05,546 --> 00:22:09,260
While talking with Da-Na,

381
00:22:10,174 --> 00:22:13,075
I realized she's not really
deeply interested in anything.

382
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:18,284
We just talk about fun things
and have light conversations.

383
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:21,012
There was no depth.

384
00:22:22,191 --> 00:22:25,301
Which girl do you
think is truly a Love Catchers?

385
00:22:27,052 --> 00:22:28,600
This is important.

386
00:22:31,161 --> 00:22:32,161
Ha-neul.

387
00:22:32,686 --> 00:22:35,722
When I see her expressions
and actions after she

388
00:22:35,747 --> 00:22:38,783
expresses her interest,
I can tell she's genuine.

389
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:42,915
(Ha-neul's honest reactions made
Jung-woo see her as a Love Catcher.)

390
00:22:43,268 --> 00:22:45,902
Who do think wrote a fake
profile about themselves?

391
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:51,401
Now that I think about it, I think
Ha-neul's profile could be fake.

392
00:22:53,279 --> 00:22:56,843
She said she's in the food service
industry, but I've never seen her cook.

393
00:22:56,868 --> 00:23:00,322
- Oh, that's true.
- I just got goosebumps.

394
00:23:00,692 --> 00:23:04,938
I'm not disagreeing with that.

395
00:23:05,137 --> 00:23:08,306
I'm suspicious, too, but
she's such a nice person.

396
00:23:08,755 --> 00:23:11,200
So I feel like she's someone
who came as a Money

397
00:23:11,225 --> 00:23:13,369
Catcher but could
change to a Love Catcher.

398
00:23:13,825 --> 00:23:15,689
- I agree.
- I'm sure about that.

399
00:23:16,494 --> 00:23:18,287
Everyone agrees with that.

400
00:23:21,998 --> 00:23:23,498
I'm really nervous.

401
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:30,335
The ones who were suspected
were Yeo-min, Da-Na, Won-jae,

402
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:34,579
Jae-hyung, Su-won, and even
though it's a bit vague, Ha-neul.

403
00:23:34,604 --> 00:23:37,187
A total of six people were called out.

404
00:23:37,212 --> 00:23:40,691
Actually, we were all
suspicious of them at some point.

405
00:23:40,814 --> 00:23:43,281
I'm curious about how
Da-Na will act after this.

406
00:23:43,306 --> 00:23:46,672
- Right.
- We know that she chose Jung-woo,

407
00:23:46,705 --> 00:23:50,238
but no one here could tell
she was interested in him.

408
00:23:50,363 --> 00:23:55,175
So I'm curious how she'll act after she was
pointed out as a possible Money Catcher.

409
00:23:57,569 --> 00:24:00,061
(Men's lodging)

410
00:24:00,629 --> 00:24:02,596
What direction should I head in?

411
00:24:03,231 --> 00:24:04,461
I think I know who to choose.

412
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:08,166
I think you do, too. You
have one on your mind.

413
00:24:09,477 --> 00:24:10,818
(Concerned)

414
00:24:11,814 --> 00:24:13,671
I think it'd be a waste so sleep tonight.

415
00:24:14,237 --> 00:24:15,753
I can't sleep tonight!

416
00:24:16,415 --> 00:24:18,978
What should we do today? Seriously?

417
00:24:20,649 --> 00:24:22,403
- I'm curious.
- Seriously.

418
00:24:22,428 --> 00:24:25,016
(Just then, mysterious women
are here to visit the Love Mansion.)

419
00:24:25,041 --> 00:24:27,510
- Love Mansion is over there.
- Thump, thump.

420
00:24:27,535 --> 00:24:28,917
It'll be fun.

421
00:24:30,365 --> 00:24:34,619
(A group of new people. What will
happen at the Love Mansion today?)

422
00:24:35,053 --> 00:24:36,053
Who are they?

423
00:24:39,057 --> 00:24:41,286
What the heck?

424
00:24:42,202 --> 00:24:44,194
- Who are they?
- What? Is someone here?

425
00:24:47,394 --> 00:24:51,263
(They've already entered the Love Mansion.)

426
00:24:52,182 --> 00:24:53,538
There are clothes over there.

427
00:24:57,575 --> 00:25:00,347
|(The mysterious women stop
in front of the women's lodging.)

428
00:25:04,535 --> 00:25:05,535
What is it?

429
00:25:06,792 --> 00:25:07,792
What is it?

430
00:25:09,472 --> 00:25:11,722
(The women are happy to see them.)

431
00:25:12,256 --> 00:25:14,741
(Who are these women?)

432
00:25:15,491 --> 00:25:19,023
(They are the women's friends.)

433
00:25:19,274 --> 00:25:21,052
The participants didn't know either.

434
00:25:21,297 --> 00:25:23,681
- They must not have known.
- It's like a surprise event.

435
00:25:24,558 --> 00:25:28,191
(Today's event: Women's Invitation)

436
00:25:28,298 --> 00:25:31,799
- I'm about to cry!
- I guess their friends are here.

437
00:25:32,178 --> 00:25:35,026
- Oh.
- They must really be here.

438
00:25:36,763 --> 00:25:39,482
(The surprising reunion
with their close friends)

439
00:25:39,507 --> 00:25:41,278
(Ha-neul's friend: Kim Ji-hyun)

440
00:25:41,303 --> 00:25:43,685
(Yeo-min's friend: Park Ju-hyun)

441
00:25:44,508 --> 00:25:47,783
(She bursts into tears as
soon as she sees her friend.)

442
00:25:48,383 --> 00:25:50,806
Why did you come all the way here?

443
00:25:50,846 --> 00:25:53,900
(In-seong's friend: Song Ye-Jin)

444
00:25:53,925 --> 00:25:56,771
(Da-na's friend: Yoon Jung-sun)

445
00:25:57,718 --> 00:25:59,956
Why are you crying?

446
00:26:00,477 --> 00:26:02,944
- Excuse me!
- Which one's your bed?

447
00:26:03,313 --> 00:26:05,075
- This one.
- This one?

448
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:06,100
Yup!

449
00:26:07,936 --> 00:26:10,421
- That's the dressing table.
- This is the dressing table?

450
00:26:10,446 --> 00:26:12,908
It's nice to do all your
makeup together here!

451
00:26:13,738 --> 00:26:16,006
Gosh, I have so much to tell you.

452
00:26:16,031 --> 00:26:17,538
I came to hear everything.

453
00:26:17,993 --> 00:26:19,793
We all became good friends.

454
00:26:20,051 --> 00:26:22,805
- You know my personality.
- Did you come here to make friends?

455
00:26:23,317 --> 00:26:24,583
She hit bull's eye!

456
00:26:25,167 --> 00:26:26,167
Let's go out.

457
00:26:27,310 --> 00:26:29,524
(Rummage)

458
00:26:32,183 --> 00:26:33,571
(Moist)

459
00:26:34,237 --> 00:26:36,724
(They prepare to greet the
guests in a speedy and simple way.)

460
00:26:36,749 --> 00:26:37,749
(Stare)

461
00:26:38,625 --> 00:26:40,156
I should take my lip balm.

462
00:26:41,613 --> 00:26:44,597
(They finished looking at the lodging.)

463
00:26:45,187 --> 00:26:47,324
(The guys go out to greet their friends.)

464
00:26:49,550 --> 00:26:51,764
- How should we sit?
- Those are the guys.

465
00:26:54,442 --> 00:26:55,442
Hello.

466
00:26:56,181 --> 00:27:00,297
- Hello.
- Hello.

467
00:27:00,785 --> 00:27:03,483
They could see things
in a more accurate light.

468
00:27:05,194 --> 00:27:08,482
They're looking at it
from a third point of view.

469
00:27:08,507 --> 00:27:10,720
"I think he likes you."

470
00:27:11,107 --> 00:27:13,151
(Then it's game over.)

471
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:15,892
- Hello.
- Hello.

472
00:27:17,158 --> 00:27:18,293
(She quickly scans.)

473
00:27:18,318 --> 00:27:22,773
- Do you want me to put these on plates?
- We'll go put these on plates.

474
00:27:22,998 --> 00:27:24,943
- Oh, really?
- This...

475
00:27:25,279 --> 00:27:26,961
It's been a while since you guys met.

476
00:27:28,543 --> 00:27:30,297
This is fun! This is so interesting!

477
00:27:30,322 --> 00:27:31,830
I guess they're really close.

478
00:27:33,724 --> 00:27:36,724
But I think I can tell
who he is right away.

479
00:27:36,749 --> 00:27:37,917
Who is it?

480
00:27:38,562 --> 00:27:41,357
The guy in the white
shirt. I'm right, aren't I?

481
00:27:42,095 --> 00:27:43,206
How'd you know?

482
00:27:43,527 --> 00:27:45,353
She recognized him right away?

483
00:27:45,378 --> 00:27:48,704
- As soon as I saw him, I could
feel his eyes on you. - Really?

484
00:27:49,074 --> 00:27:51,827
- He was like that from the beginning.
- From the first day?

485
00:27:52,211 --> 00:27:54,585
- From the very beginning.
- Do you feel the same way?

486
00:27:57,138 --> 00:27:58,598
How about we sit down first?

487
00:27:59,972 --> 00:28:04,212
(Ha-neul can't really respond to the
question "Do you feel the same way?")

488
00:28:04,844 --> 00:28:07,044
Do you think he's a Love Catcher?

489
00:28:08,991 --> 00:28:11,269
- He seemed like a Money Catcher at first.
- Really?

490
00:28:11,913 --> 00:28:13,494
But I think he's a Love Catcher now.

491
00:28:14,664 --> 00:28:17,537
You know I have good hunches,
right? I'll see him talk first.

492
00:28:17,922 --> 00:28:20,461
I'll take a good look at him.

493
00:28:20,829 --> 00:28:22,762
Wow, she's a reliable friend.

494
00:28:23,943 --> 00:28:26,635
The guy I had something with left.
And this all ends tomorrow.

495
00:28:26,924 --> 00:28:30,376
I kept going straight
with him from the first day.

496
00:28:30,401 --> 00:28:31,982
- The one who was eliminated?
- Yeah.

497
00:28:32,007 --> 00:28:35,031
- He was going for you?
- He approached me on the first day.

498
00:28:35,225 --> 00:28:39,687
I thought he was a good guy, so we
kept getting close, but he was eliminated.

499
00:28:42,122 --> 00:28:44,722
I feel really empty without him around.

500
00:28:47,145 --> 00:28:50,090
(Everyone is overflowing
with laughter as usual.)

501
00:28:50,632 --> 00:28:55,186
(And In-seong floats around
them like a secluded island.)

502
00:28:55,835 --> 00:28:57,493
It's a bit complicated.

503
00:28:58,819 --> 00:29:03,243
Jung-woo was the one I liked,
so I don't know what to do now.

504
00:29:03,542 --> 00:29:06,666
And if I express interest
in another guy, they can

505
00:29:06,691 --> 00:29:09,814
think that I'm doing it just
because he's gone now.

506
00:29:10,211 --> 00:29:12,938
It's possible, so I'm kind
of concerned about that.

507
00:29:15,334 --> 00:29:18,538
(In-seong feels Jung-woo's
emptiness everywhere.)

508
00:29:18,563 --> 00:29:22,199
Out of all people, why did
he have to be eliminated?

509
00:29:22,743 --> 00:29:23,743
I know.

510
00:29:24,922 --> 00:29:30,358
Right now, I'm kind of
stuck between two people.

511
00:29:30,383 --> 00:29:32,252
The two guys you mentioned earlier.

512
00:29:32,277 --> 00:29:33,831
There's one more person, huh?

513
00:29:33,856 --> 00:29:36,383
Did she add Ji-min after
their conversation earlier?

514
00:29:36,728 --> 00:29:40,458
Which one are you the
most interested in right now?

515
00:29:40,483 --> 00:29:46,637
Me? The one I originally was interested
in was Won-jae, who's 23 years old.

516
00:29:46,662 --> 00:29:47,662
He's young.

517
00:29:48,152 --> 00:29:50,852
There's someone I talked
to for the first time today.

518
00:29:50,877 --> 00:29:53,623
But he has such a nice personality.

519
00:29:54,244 --> 00:29:57,896
It's the first time I had a nonstop
conversation with someone.

520
00:29:59,315 --> 00:30:02,251
- Wow. - I felt like our
conversations really flowed.

521
00:30:02,896 --> 00:30:05,292
But you feel comfortable
with the younger guy?

522
00:30:06,176 --> 00:30:07,176
I don't know.

523
00:30:07,201 --> 00:30:09,384
- You're still thinking.
- Ji-min was comfortable, too.

524
00:30:10,523 --> 00:30:13,871
Won-jae is trying to make
me feel comfortable, but

525
00:30:13,896 --> 00:30:17,374
for some reason, our
conversations don't really flow.

526
00:30:17,399 --> 00:30:19,391
- So no chemistry?
- We don't have chemistry.

527
00:30:19,659 --> 00:30:24,381
But it was really
comfortable to talk to Ji-min.

528
00:30:24,406 --> 00:30:27,307
I didn't have to think
about what to say next.

529
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:32,096
- It's complicated. - It is. I really
have a lot on my mind.

530
00:30:33,744 --> 00:30:36,253
We're able to hear their
thoughts because of their friends.

531
00:30:36,645 --> 00:30:40,732
("Women's Invitation" with their friends)

532
00:30:41,416 --> 00:30:44,316
(Finally, they've all gathered together.)

533
00:30:45,504 --> 00:30:48,536
What to do? It's peaceful but
not peaceful at the same time.

534
00:30:49,342 --> 00:30:50,913
Gosh, what will they talk about?

535
00:30:50,938 --> 00:30:53,811
I think we should introduce ourselves.

536
00:30:56,532 --> 00:31:00,190
The guys will go first since
it's your first time meeting us.

537
00:31:00,870 --> 00:31:03,137
I'm 30, and my name is Ahn Ji-min.

538
00:31:03,570 --> 00:31:04,903
It's nice to meet you.

539
00:31:06,438 --> 00:31:10,601
I'm 29 years old, and my name
is Jung Su-won. I'm from Busan.

540
00:31:10,626 --> 00:31:11,626
That's about it.

541
00:31:14,939 --> 00:31:17,535
I'm 23-year-old Kang Won-jae.

542
00:31:19,887 --> 00:31:21,754
Isn't he from "Produce 101"?

543
00:31:22,094 --> 00:31:23,684
He kind of feels like that, huh?

544
00:31:24,253 --> 00:31:25,742
(Are they talking about me?)

545
00:31:25,767 --> 00:31:27,196
He appeared on "Steel Troops."

546
00:31:29,333 --> 00:31:31,890
- She asked if you were from "Produce 101."
- "Produce 101"?

547
00:31:31,915 --> 00:31:34,940
I'm sorry. I thought he looked familiar.

548
00:31:34,965 --> 00:31:36,976
- Same here.
- But he's from "Steel Troops."

549
00:31:37,485 --> 00:31:40,432
(Yeo-min can't stop looking at the
warm and friendly Da-Na and Won-jae.)

550
00:31:40,457 --> 00:31:42,864
- From some point on, it
seems like she's given up. - Yeah.

551
00:31:42,889 --> 00:31:43,889
It's uncomfortable.

552
00:31:45,056 --> 00:31:47,360
I'm 32 years old, and my
name is Seo Jae-hyung.

553
00:31:50,946 --> 00:31:53,930
Can you tell us about your friends?

554
00:31:55,022 --> 00:31:56,220
Wow, good idea.

555
00:31:56,705 --> 00:32:00,285
- Like, what kind of person Ha-neul is.
- Oh, the opposite?

556
00:32:02,148 --> 00:32:03,449
(Curious)

557
00:32:04,350 --> 00:32:07,389
Ha-neul has a fixed ideal type.

558
00:32:09,227 --> 00:32:13,301
She's very clear about it, and
there's a certain type of face she likes.

559
00:32:15,131 --> 00:32:17,531
- What type?
- The puppy-face type.

560
00:32:17,944 --> 00:32:22,896
Not the baby kind but
the slightly mature kind.

561
00:32:23,822 --> 00:32:25,052
That's Su-won!

562
00:32:25,077 --> 00:32:28,387
Is there someone who's close
to that type out of the four of us?

563
00:32:28,700 --> 00:32:30,517
His tone sounded like...

564
00:32:30,796 --> 00:32:33,566
Is there someone who's close
to that type out of the four of us?

565
00:32:33,718 --> 00:32:36,808
His eyes! There's laser coming out of them.

566
00:32:37,494 --> 00:32:39,748
They're getting urgent
'cause there's no time.

567
00:32:39,773 --> 00:32:43,228
Is there someone who's close
to that type out of the four of us?

568
00:32:43,253 --> 00:32:44,720
Out of the four of us?

569
00:32:44,874 --> 00:32:46,453
Even though it might not be him.

570
00:32:48,104 --> 00:32:50,451
(Who will she choose
as Ha-neul's ideal type?)

571
00:32:50,930 --> 00:32:52,959
(Anticipating)

572
00:32:55,609 --> 00:32:56,792
There are two of them.

573
00:32:58,278 --> 00:32:59,744
There are two of them.

574
00:33:00,130 --> 00:33:01,900
- Can I pick them both?
- Sure.

575
00:33:02,767 --> 00:33:05,666
(Without a choice, all of
them are looking forward to it.)

576
00:33:05,691 --> 00:33:09,112
- If she picks Ji-min and Su-won...
- It'd be wild.

577
00:33:09,459 --> 00:33:15,069
I think it's these two.

578
00:33:16,344 --> 00:33:17,344
Oh my god.

579
00:33:18,111 --> 00:33:21,682
They have the face types that she likes.

580
00:33:22,050 --> 00:33:23,335
Oh, the puppy-face type?

581
00:33:25,378 --> 00:33:28,554
(Even if he's chosen,
he has mixed feelings.)

582
00:33:28,724 --> 00:33:36,500
Yeo-min is so sweet that I
always says she's No. 1 wife material.

583
00:33:36,525 --> 00:33:38,280
- Really?
- She's No. 1 wife material.

584
00:33:38,305 --> 00:33:40,353
She's good at taking care of herself.

585
00:33:40,641 --> 00:33:42,323
She likes working out.

586
00:33:42,427 --> 00:33:46,227
If you go to her place,
everything's organized very well.

587
00:33:47,466 --> 00:33:48,886
She's No. 1 wife material.

588
00:33:50,011 --> 00:33:53,642
(The friend who knows Yeo-min
the best really showed her charms.)

589
00:33:54,491 --> 00:33:59,627
She says she likes good-looking guys,

590
00:33:59,652 --> 00:34:01,756
but when I see the guys she dates...

591
00:34:01,972 --> 00:34:06,935
Rather then their looks, I think she goes
for something else, like their personality.

592
00:34:07,813 --> 00:34:12,463
She likes Jay Park.

593
00:34:12,488 --> 00:34:13,738
Oh, Jay Park?

594
00:34:14,234 --> 00:34:16,955
Someone who's not in
real life. Someone like that.

595
00:34:17,890 --> 00:34:21,720
(For some reason, Da-Na
seems to have high standards.)

596
00:34:22,057 --> 00:34:24,868
Today's the day before the last day.

597
00:34:25,171 --> 00:34:27,353
(It's regrettable.)

598
00:34:28,842 --> 00:34:30,390
To tomorrow. Cheers.

599
00:34:30,573 --> 00:34:34,914
- Cheers!
- It's nice to meet you.

600
00:34:35,212 --> 00:34:37,046
Cheers!

601
00:34:40,862 --> 00:34:43,799
- Should we chat while eating?
- Sounds good.

602
00:34:43,824 --> 00:34:46,366
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

603
00:34:46,391 --> 00:34:47,391
Enjoy.

604
00:34:51,722 --> 00:34:53,237
- Da-Na, here.
- Thank you.

605
00:34:53,262 --> 00:34:55,859
(He takes good care of Da-Na.)

606
00:34:56,902 --> 00:34:58,635
I want to eat salmon, too.

607
00:34:58,868 --> 00:35:02,191
(Yeo-min slightly gives a hint to Won-jae,
who is scooping food for everyone.)

608
00:35:02,472 --> 00:35:07,292
- Have you ever tried the salmon?
It's really good. - Really?

609
00:35:08,914 --> 00:35:10,970
I ate some on my way here.

610
00:35:10,995 --> 00:35:12,507
- It's so good.
- You ate some?

611
00:35:13,251 --> 00:35:16,269
- So that's why you were late.
- Yeah. I was busy eating.

612
00:35:17,087 --> 00:35:20,887
(Right away, Da-Na eats the
salmon that Won-jae got her.)

613
00:35:21,349 --> 00:35:22,349
It's yummy!

614
00:35:22,934 --> 00:35:24,278
(Pleased)

615
00:35:25,615 --> 00:35:28,108
I didn't really hear it, but how
are you friends with Ha-neul?

616
00:35:28,133 --> 00:35:30,747
- Oh, Ha-neul and I...
- How did we become friends?

617
00:35:30,772 --> 00:35:31,905
I don't remember.

618
00:35:32,075 --> 00:35:33,686
- You don't remember?
- No.

619
00:35:33,711 --> 00:35:37,545
We weren't really close, and
we didn't talk to each other much.

620
00:35:38,384 --> 00:35:41,702
But after hanging out a few times, one
day... We went to the Han River, right?

621
00:35:41,727 --> 00:35:44,093
- Yeah.
- How long have you been friends?

622
00:35:44,723 --> 00:35:47,151
- Four years? Three to four years?
- It's been a while then.

623
00:35:47,176 --> 00:35:48,765
Is she your closest friend now?

624
00:35:50,379 --> 00:35:52,117
- Yeah.
- Why did you hesitate?

625
00:35:52,142 --> 00:35:53,818
Feel free to ask me anything.

626
00:35:55,806 --> 00:35:57,575
I think I can answer you that much.

627
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:59,935
- Su-won is too far.
- He's way too far.

628
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:03,963
But when you came here, you
saw the girls for the first time.

629
00:36:03,988 --> 00:36:06,076
What were your first
impressions? I'm so curious.

630
00:36:06,101 --> 00:36:08,037
Did you guys talk about this already?

631
00:36:08,748 --> 00:36:12,026
- Our first impression of each other?
- Yes, how was it?

632
00:36:16,154 --> 00:36:17,320
At first,

633
00:36:18,487 --> 00:36:21,488
Da-Na looked really chic and cold,

634
00:36:21,881 --> 00:36:23,579
and I thought she was hard to approach.

635
00:36:23,604 --> 00:36:27,955
But she's down-to-earth, fun, and clumsy.

636
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:30,186
She's warm-hearted.

637
00:36:30,304 --> 00:36:32,549
So that's why I thought she was charming.

638
00:36:34,241 --> 00:36:35,241
She's charming.

639
00:36:35,959 --> 00:36:38,548
And as for Ha-neul,

640
00:36:39,330 --> 00:36:44,930
she gave me a really strong impression.
Her eyes, nose, and mouth are so prominent.

641
00:36:45,399 --> 00:36:47,366
She was impactful.

642
00:36:48,132 --> 00:36:50,801
I thought she'd be hard to
approach, but a minute after I

643
00:36:50,826 --> 00:36:53,632
entered the room, I realized
she's someone easy to be around.

644
00:36:54,274 --> 00:36:58,059
Seriously. She smiles to people
even though she's just met them.

645
00:36:58,084 --> 00:37:01,078
I could tell she was trying
to treat everyone warmly.

646
00:37:01,103 --> 00:37:04,319
I had a really good first
impression of her. It was nice.

647
00:37:06,016 --> 00:37:09,000
I was the first one to arrive.

648
00:37:10,858 --> 00:37:11,858
He's talking.

649
00:37:12,086 --> 00:37:16,619
When she entered the room, I thought
she'd be nice to seduce.

650
00:37:17,169 --> 00:37:18,169
What the heck?

651
00:37:19,147 --> 00:37:20,355
"Seduce"?

652
00:37:20,380 --> 00:37:25,400
He probably tried to break the
ice by saying it in a witty manner.

653
00:37:25,425 --> 00:37:28,507
- The Su-won we know isn't like that.
- Exactly.

654
00:37:28,532 --> 00:37:31,690
He's someone straightforward
who sincerely looks for love.

655
00:37:31,715 --> 00:37:33,892
I think he said it like that on purpose.

656
00:37:35,396 --> 00:37:41,777
When she entered the room, I thought
she'd be nice to seduce.

657
00:37:41,802 --> 00:37:43,269
He's coming on strong!

658
00:37:43,562 --> 00:37:45,609
That's what I thought at first.

659
00:37:47,309 --> 00:37:49,495
Oh my god!

660
00:37:51,134 --> 00:37:55,039
Wow, he's really coming on strong today.
He's not usually like that.

661
00:37:55,064 --> 00:37:56,472
He's doing this for the first time.

662
00:37:56,497 --> 00:38:00,307
That's right! I agree with
In-seong. He's not usually like that.

663
00:38:01,434 --> 00:38:05,568
(For some reason, "Women's
Invitation" was really passionate.)

664
00:38:06,009 --> 00:38:08,984
(Soon, the hot sun has gone down.)

665
00:38:09,410 --> 00:38:12,280
(It's time to finish talking
before they part ways.)

666
00:38:12,936 --> 00:38:14,174
It's somewhat regrettable.

667
00:38:15,692 --> 00:38:18,637
Who's the guy you're interested in?
That's what I really wanted to know.

668
00:38:18,911 --> 00:38:21,577
If you only look at their
appearances, who do you think it is?

669
00:38:21,881 --> 00:38:24,825
Honestly, right when I saw
him, I thought it was... the 23-year-old.

670
00:38:25,457 --> 00:38:28,123
- Really?
- Just. I just had a feeling.

671
00:38:29,937 --> 00:38:32,310
Friends definitely know!

672
00:38:32,876 --> 00:38:33,876
You're right.

673
00:38:34,994 --> 00:38:36,327
- For real?
- Yeah.

674
00:38:36,573 --> 00:38:38,675
- I knew you would think that way.
- Right?

675
00:38:39,035 --> 00:38:41,979
That's why I kept looking at him.

676
00:38:42,141 --> 00:38:47,731
I wanted to talk with a lot of
people as quickly as I could.

677
00:38:48,060 --> 00:38:51,411
So even if I was interested in
Won-jae, I tried to talk with other guys.

678
00:38:51,436 --> 00:38:54,540
But in the meantime,
he kept waiting for me.

679
00:38:55,863 --> 00:38:59,996
So I got certain that I liked
him and was about to express it.

680
00:39:00,201 --> 00:39:03,573
But on that day, with another girl...

681
00:39:04,258 --> 00:39:06,497
- Something happened between them?
- Yeah.

682
00:39:06,522 --> 00:39:08,056
Aww, how upsetting.

683
00:39:09,290 --> 00:39:10,756
So there's no one now?

684
00:39:11,029 --> 00:39:13,060
I'm just going to keep choosing him.

685
00:39:13,627 --> 00:39:16,561
- What about him?
- I don't know about him.

686
00:39:16,995 --> 00:39:18,728
I don't know how he feels.

687
00:39:19,316 --> 00:39:20,916
Is he thinking of Da-Na?

688
00:39:21,389 --> 00:39:27,423
So right now,Won-jae is the
one you're interested in the most?

689
00:39:30,526 --> 00:39:31,526
I'm not sure.

690
00:39:31,803 --> 00:39:33,900
Honestly, I'm not sure about anything.

691
00:39:34,268 --> 00:39:37,085
But Won-jae seemed to
take care of you a lot earlier.

692
00:39:37,295 --> 00:39:39,866
- Oh, really?
- He took care of you a lot.

693
00:39:39,891 --> 00:39:41,193
- Seriously?
- Yeah, he did.

694
00:39:42,396 --> 00:39:44,776
I guess their friends
really do see everything.

695
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:50,400
- You don't need a jacket?
- No, I'm fine. I'm not cold.

696
00:39:51,563 --> 00:39:52,873
I thought so.

697
00:39:54,996 --> 00:39:57,982
We have a certain image
when it comes to younger guys,

698
00:39:58,575 --> 00:40:02,042
but it didn't feel like you
guys had a big age gap.

699
00:40:03,942 --> 00:40:07,101
- Yeah.
- You just need to go with your heart.

700
00:40:07,126 --> 00:40:09,833
- Don't try to think so much.
- Okay.

701
00:40:14,079 --> 00:40:19,262
So what's going on? Is your heart changing?

702
00:40:20,103 --> 00:40:21,793
It's complicated. I don't know.

703
00:40:22,327 --> 00:40:27,708
When I first saw Su-won, he
seemed like a Love Catcher to me.

704
00:40:28,326 --> 00:40:33,048
But you know that strong
remark he made earlier?

705
00:40:34,045 --> 00:40:35,379
Why did he say that?

706
00:40:35,450 --> 00:40:38,380
After I heard that, I was like,
"Wow, he's coming on that strongly?"

707
00:40:39,114 --> 00:40:40,114
Is he...?

708
00:40:41,185 --> 00:40:43,410
- Is he a Money Catcher?
- I was so flustered, too.

709
00:40:43,945 --> 00:40:47,302
I thought Love Catchers
would be a bit more careful.

710
00:40:47,327 --> 00:40:52,831
Right. That's why I wondered why he
would go so far during our first meeting.

711
00:40:52,856 --> 00:40:55,350
"How could he be so certain?
What does he know about me?"

712
00:40:55,382 --> 00:40:58,982
The more I see him, the more
he seemed like a Money Catcher,

713
00:40:59,007 --> 00:41:01,516
but he could unexpectedly
be a Love Catcher.

714
00:41:01,873 --> 00:41:03,770
(Is that so?)

715
00:41:04,992 --> 00:41:08,436
Let's say he is a Money Catcher.

716
00:41:09,250 --> 00:41:12,813
I still wouldn't think everything
he did to me were lies.

717
00:41:14,796 --> 00:41:21,454
Those moments could have been sincere.

718
00:41:21,851 --> 00:41:23,477
I don't think it's all acting.

719
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:25,200
That's true.

720
00:41:25,884 --> 00:41:27,846
So I wouldn't really be bothered by it.

721
00:41:28,942 --> 00:41:30,783
I don't think I'll be that hurt either.

722
00:41:34,171 --> 00:41:37,438
- She still has feelings for Su-won.
- She does.

723
00:41:37,463 --> 00:41:40,906
- She didn't fully turn away from him.
- But why isn't she accepting him?

724
00:41:41,953 --> 00:41:46,422
(The friends left, and there are eight
people at the Love Mansion again.)

725
00:41:46,447 --> 00:41:48,517
- I'm hungry.
- You're gonna eat something, right?

726
00:41:49,648 --> 00:41:52,943
(Su-won is preparing light dinner.)

727
00:41:55,290 --> 00:41:56,765
(Slowly)

728
00:41:59,373 --> 00:42:02,706
- Are you gonna eat?
- Yeah, just a couple bites.

729
00:42:03,646 --> 00:42:04,646
Alright.

730
00:42:05,261 --> 00:42:08,817
That means she'll have half a ramen.

731
00:42:14,114 --> 00:42:16,786
(Su-won puts the chapagetti
he made in front of Ha-neul.)

732
00:42:16,811 --> 00:42:19,678
- It's not good if it's cold.
- Thank you.

733
00:42:22,576 --> 00:42:25,500
(Everyone is enjoying it.)

734
00:42:26,219 --> 00:42:28,044
(But Ha-neul isn't even taking a bite.)

735
00:42:28,069 --> 00:42:30,352
I think he put it in front of
her because he thought she

736
00:42:30,377 --> 00:42:32,539
was going to eat it. Why
doesn't she look interested?

737
00:42:33,615 --> 00:42:35,131
(Glance)

738
00:42:36,468 --> 00:42:38,261
They have to hurry up and talk.

739
00:42:38,892 --> 00:42:41,899
(For some reason, Ha-neul
doesn't seem to be in a good mood.)

740
00:42:43,357 --> 00:42:47,380
When she entered the room, I
thought she'd be nice to seduce.

741
00:42:47,941 --> 00:42:49,441
Is he a Money Catcher?

742
00:42:50,333 --> 00:42:53,721
I thought Love Catchers
would be a bit more careful.

743
00:42:54,638 --> 00:42:56,725
She must be concerned
about what her friend said.

744
00:42:57,431 --> 00:42:59,934
Why aren't you eating? You
said you were going to have some.

745
00:42:59,966 --> 00:43:01,750
I'm too lazy.

746
00:43:02,004 --> 00:43:04,150
(Lazy...?)

747
00:43:08,142 --> 00:43:11,840
To not eat chapagetti
when it's in front of you...

748
00:43:11,865 --> 00:43:12,932
It's impossible.

749
00:43:12,957 --> 00:43:15,170
- It's not easy.
- She's probably thinking about it.

750
00:43:17,309 --> 00:43:19,452
(Uncomfortable)

751
00:43:20,902 --> 00:43:25,093
(Dinner continues in a cold atmosphere.)

752
00:43:26,320 --> 00:43:30,200
(Meanwhile, Da-Na seems
to have a lot on her mind.)

753
00:43:32,992 --> 00:43:35,470
- Isn't it the first time we
saw her like this? - Yes.

754
00:43:36,012 --> 00:43:37,591
Ugh, my head hurts.

755
00:43:40,928 --> 00:43:44,034
(She gets up as if she's
made up her mind...)

756
00:43:46,427 --> 00:43:47,554
(Stare)

757
00:43:47,579 --> 00:43:49,706
(Who is she looking at?)

758
00:43:50,947 --> 00:43:53,494
- Are you sick?
- No, I'm not.

759
00:43:54,078 --> 00:43:55,308
(Worried)

760
00:43:56,516 --> 00:43:57,826
(Let's go out.)

761
00:43:58,170 --> 00:44:00,304
- Who is she talking to?
- Jae-hyung?

762
00:44:00,329 --> 00:44:01,815
She said that to Jae-hyung?

763
00:44:02,781 --> 00:44:05,397
(Da-Na wanted to talk to Jae-hyung.)

764
00:44:06,433 --> 00:44:08,338
Uh-oh. Won-jae.

765
00:44:09,765 --> 00:44:11,983
(Da-Na and Jae-hyung leave together.)

766
00:44:12,852 --> 00:44:14,535
He must be so bothered by that.

767
00:44:17,382 --> 00:44:19,603
Oh, thank you.

768
00:44:21,042 --> 00:44:23,822
I'm so curious to find out
what they're going to talk about.

769
00:44:26,145 --> 00:44:30,994
You made a lot of preparations
for our date yesterday,

770
00:44:31,286 --> 00:44:34,325
and I know you kept taking care of me.

771
00:44:34,357 --> 00:44:37,344
I know you're a really
amazing person, but...

772
00:44:38,245 --> 00:44:40,982
- Oh no!
- She said "but."

773
00:44:41,007 --> 00:44:44,036
- But he's out of the game? That's sad.
- I have a bad feeling about this.

774
00:44:44,061 --> 00:44:47,834
I know you're a really
amazing person, but...

775
00:44:49,725 --> 00:44:54,648
I don't think you're the one for me, so I
felt like I had to let you know right away.

776
00:44:56,304 --> 00:44:59,439
(She politely rejects him.)

777
00:45:01,428 --> 00:45:02,428
Really?

778
00:45:02,952 --> 00:45:05,055
- Oh no.
- Goodness.

779
00:45:06,665 --> 00:45:10,990
Yes, but I like these
kinds of relationships.

780
00:45:13,140 --> 00:45:15,798
The ones that are fun and very comfortable.

781
00:45:16,524 --> 00:45:21,351
I'm not that young, but I enjoy
dates that young people go on.

782
00:45:21,712 --> 00:45:25,445
That means she wasn't
comfortable when she was with him.

783
00:45:25,946 --> 00:45:31,413
Honestly speaking, there wasn't anyone I
was curious or wanted to know about here.

784
00:45:32,810 --> 00:45:33,810
Not really.

785
00:45:34,845 --> 00:45:36,471
But when after you came...

786
00:45:38,380 --> 00:45:42,114
I got curious about you, and
I became interested in you.

787
00:45:43,321 --> 00:45:48,298
That's why I asked you on a date that day.
I knew a lot of guys would pick you.

788
00:45:50,759 --> 00:45:58,128
I knew that, but I was going to ask
you out anyway, so that's what I did.

789
00:46:00,251 --> 00:46:03,539
But before you came, I was
more nervous than expected.

790
00:46:04,607 --> 00:46:06,606
- Are you waiting for her?
- Yes.

791
00:46:07,157 --> 00:46:10,252
You must be nervous.
I'm curious what kind of person she is.

792
00:46:10,921 --> 00:46:12,787
My mouth is growing dry.

793
00:46:14,989 --> 00:46:16,922
I don't normally get nervous.

794
00:46:17,914 --> 00:46:22,486
Regardless of where I
am, I never get nervous.

795
00:46:22,960 --> 00:46:26,419
But that's how I felt with you.

796
00:46:27,846 --> 00:46:34,075
I know you're an amazing person.
I felt that, and I told you that, too.

797
00:46:34,702 --> 00:46:38,090
I'm aware of that,
but... how do I put it...?

798
00:46:39,682 --> 00:46:44,131
Most of all, my feelings were
the most important thing to me.

799
00:46:44,499 --> 00:46:49,268
And I just expressed them to you...

800
00:46:50,854 --> 00:46:51,854
I'm sorry.

801
00:46:52,742 --> 00:46:54,632
There's no reason for you to apologize.

802
00:46:56,638 --> 00:47:00,542
If they had only talked sooner...

803
00:47:00,567 --> 00:47:02,349
They had the wrong timing, too.

804
00:47:04,620 --> 00:47:06,264
It's suddenly raining.

805
00:47:07,769 --> 00:47:11,476
(Like someone's heart, the
rain is furiously pouring down.)

806
00:47:11,794 --> 00:47:14,685
(And these three are sitting in silence.)

807
00:47:14,710 --> 00:47:18,253
- Oh, it's that scene!
- The one from the first episode.

808
00:47:18,278 --> 00:47:22,192
- We're seeing the full thing now.
- So Ji-min was there, too.

809
00:47:26,444 --> 00:47:27,516
(Glance)

810
00:47:31,300 --> 00:47:33,418
(Suffocating silence)

811
00:47:33,743 --> 00:47:36,199
They have to talk now.
No matter what happens.

812
00:47:37,546 --> 00:47:39,346
You both don't really talk.

813
00:47:40,994 --> 00:47:42,534
Yeah, we don't really talk.

814
00:47:42,559 --> 00:47:43,851
Did you guys talk too much?

815
00:47:43,876 --> 00:47:45,893
No. Su-won normally doesn't talk a lot.

816
00:47:47,048 --> 00:47:49,119
I talk if I have to.

817
00:47:50,718 --> 00:47:51,718
Yeah.

818
00:47:54,034 --> 00:47:56,127
If I like someone, I want
to keep talking with them.

819
00:47:57,090 --> 00:47:58,749
He talked with Ha-neul the most.

820
00:48:00,201 --> 00:48:01,775
That's not the case for everyone.

821
00:48:03,016 --> 00:48:04,016
(Glance)

822
00:48:05,104 --> 00:48:06,771
Su-won doesn't talk much.

823
00:48:08,422 --> 00:48:10,776
I guess there's nothing
he's curious about anymore.

824
00:48:11,397 --> 00:48:12,620
That's not true.

825
00:48:13,944 --> 00:48:16,798
(Their uncomfortable
atmosphere can't be ignored.)

826
00:48:17,628 --> 00:48:23,400
Honestly, before we came in here, I didn't
think there'd be such intense emotions.

827
00:48:24,660 --> 00:48:30,425
But this is more intense
than I thought it'd be.

828
00:48:31,580 --> 00:48:32,713
It's fascinating.

829
00:48:33,844 --> 00:48:37,550
Or maybe it's because
we were always together.

830
00:48:39,262 --> 00:48:40,529
I'm getting pissed.

831
00:48:41,048 --> 00:48:42,333
(Startled)

832
00:48:42,531 --> 00:48:43,706
(Glance)

833
00:48:45,713 --> 00:48:47,220
Why did he turn out this way?

834
00:48:55,563 --> 00:48:56,563
(Stand)

835
00:48:57,104 --> 00:48:58,167
(Glance)

836
00:48:59,330 --> 00:49:01,140
Ji-min must be uncomfortable, too.

837
00:49:01,165 --> 00:49:03,198
(Ji-min leaves the room.)

838
00:49:04,711 --> 00:49:08,668
(It's just them at the table now.)

839
00:49:10,612 --> 00:49:12,652
Since he's not here, I'll say it.

840
00:49:15,968 --> 00:49:17,833
Do you have a lot on your mind...

841
00:49:19,729 --> 00:49:23,036
because of someone else
or because of what I did?

842
00:49:24,038 --> 00:49:25,673
Can you at least tell me that?

843
00:49:28,481 --> 00:49:34,322
To you, does it seem like I'm
interested in someone else?

844
00:49:35,552 --> 00:49:37,734
Is that why you're so anxious?

845
00:49:39,087 --> 00:49:41,666
It's not that I think you're
interested in someone.

846
00:49:41,972 --> 00:49:44,733
I feel like...

847
00:49:47,780 --> 00:49:51,034
Ji-min had feelings
for you in the beginning.

848
00:49:51,059 --> 00:49:52,059
That's how I felt.

849
00:49:54,128 --> 00:49:57,365
He asked me if I was interested in you.

850
00:49:58,058 --> 00:49:59,845
I think your ideal type is here then.

851
00:50:00,332 --> 00:50:05,172
We talked on the way here, and
her personality didn't seem bad.

852
00:50:05,932 --> 00:50:08,466
Right. I can tell she's down-to-earth.

853
00:50:10,518 --> 00:50:16,811
Was he not able to express his
interest in you because I said that?

854
00:50:17,540 --> 00:50:19,683
Anyway, I don't what it is.

855
00:50:20,425 --> 00:50:22,359
All I can do is make guesses.

856
00:50:22,586 --> 00:50:26,109
He's trying to make it seem
as if you guys are close friends.

857
00:50:28,267 --> 00:50:34,871
But according to my standards and
assumptions, that's not what you guys are.

858
00:50:36,958 --> 00:50:38,798
I think...

859
00:50:40,703 --> 00:50:43,501
that a part of him does like you.

860
00:50:46,246 --> 00:50:48,269
I'm bothered by Ji-min.

861
00:50:49,663 --> 00:50:52,781
We're all living under one roof,
and when we're all together...

862
00:50:54,469 --> 00:50:56,167
- Wanna go out?
- Sure.

863
00:50:57,352 --> 00:50:58,620
(Bugged)

864
00:50:59,226 --> 00:51:00,650
Let's go to the first floor.

865
00:51:00,675 --> 00:51:01,675
Sure.

866
00:51:01,840 --> 00:51:03,507
They left together again.

867
00:51:04,255 --> 00:51:05,422
(Concerned)

868
00:51:06,028 --> 00:51:09,298
Most of the time, it was
Ji-min who talked to her first.

869
00:51:09,563 --> 00:51:15,677
We're both men, so I can't help
but be bugged by that.

870
00:51:16,667 --> 00:51:20,143
It's understandable for
him to misunderstand.

871
00:51:20,168 --> 00:51:22,566
They spent too much alone time together.

872
00:51:22,591 --> 00:51:25,124
They did. He could get the wrong idea.

873
00:51:26,845 --> 00:51:30,249
And in the beginning, you
said there were two guys.

874
00:51:30,394 --> 00:51:33,284
You didn't tell me who the other guy was.

875
00:51:33,852 --> 00:51:40,664
But today, your friend
mentioned the type of guy you liked.

876
00:51:41,456 --> 00:51:48,371
Then I'd think that my speculations, or my
imaginations, are somewhat correct. Right?

877
00:51:49,496 --> 00:51:51,599
So he fit all the puzzle pieces together.

878
00:51:53,245 --> 00:51:54,745
And to some certain extent...

879
00:51:57,478 --> 00:51:59,271
you're interested in Ji-min, aren't you?

880
00:52:00,943 --> 00:52:04,197
That's the biggest question.
What does Ji-min mean to her?

881
00:52:04,222 --> 00:52:07,280
- Please just spill it! - Yes.

882
00:52:08,722 --> 00:52:10,435
And to some certain extent...

883
00:52:12,943 --> 00:52:15,250
you're interested in Ji-min, aren't you?

884
00:52:17,755 --> 00:52:21,548
Then would you not have asked
Da-Na out if I hadn't done that?

885
00:52:24,492 --> 00:52:27,833
(She's not giving him an answer.)

886
00:52:28,537 --> 00:52:30,474
But you know you were selfish, too.

887
00:52:31,841 --> 00:52:33,508
In my position,

888
00:52:34,644 --> 00:52:36,668
I did express my interest in you.

889
00:52:38,205 --> 00:52:41,713
But I took a direct him from that.

890
00:52:43,163 --> 00:52:47,378
You knew what you did was wrong
to me, and yet, you did it anyway.

891
00:52:51,131 --> 00:52:53,775
The one time he went to Da-Na
turned into something like this...

892
00:52:54,481 --> 00:52:58,865
(Does Ha-neul want to
push Su-won away like this?)

893
00:52:59,307 --> 00:53:01,275
Could I...

894
00:53:02,268 --> 00:53:03,268
trust him?

895
00:53:03,958 --> 00:53:06,558
I don't like people who make me uneasy.

896
00:53:12,769 --> 00:53:16,147
(Eventually, Ha-neul leaves the room...)

897
00:53:17,240 --> 00:53:20,532
(The two become distant again.)

898
00:53:21,486 --> 00:53:24,888
(Is it too late to go back?)

899
00:53:29,364 --> 00:53:31,998
(He feels a wave of frustration
about their severed conversation.)

900
00:53:32,023 --> 00:53:33,603
They're not able to talk it out.

901
00:53:33,628 --> 00:53:36,772
Is it because we see their conversation
in clips? It didn't end really cleanly.

902
00:53:36,797 --> 00:53:38,369
(Their conversation
is uncomfortable!)

903
00:53:38,394 --> 00:53:44,075
But Ha-neul didn't give a
clear answer about Ji-min.

904
00:53:44,100 --> 00:53:51,244
Su-won said he didn't know he would
experience such intense feelings here.

905
00:53:51,269 --> 00:53:54,585
So he came as a Money Catcher, but
he wants to change to a Love Catcher.

906
00:53:54,610 --> 00:53:58,803
Yet, he's not sure of their feelings,
so he wants to keep talking with her.

907
00:53:58,828 --> 00:54:00,161
That seems possible.

908
00:54:00,186 --> 00:54:01,940
(That makes sense.)

909
00:54:01,965 --> 00:54:04,461
Then what about Ji-min's feelings?

910
00:54:04,486 --> 00:54:07,931
I definitely think he's into Ha-neul.

911
00:54:08,984 --> 00:54:15,907
Ha-neul is the one he likes, but I
think he'll choose Da-Na for the money.

912
00:54:18,282 --> 00:54:20,891
(The pouring rain has
no intention to stop.)

913
00:54:22,031 --> 00:54:25,632
(The raindrops are growing thicker.)

914
00:54:25,962 --> 00:54:27,986
- Did you talk a lot with the others?
- Me?

915
00:54:29,933 --> 00:54:32,871
- He's with Da-Na. - I think this
conversation will be very important.

916
00:54:33,573 --> 00:54:35,859
- Did you talk a lot with the others?
- Me?

917
00:54:36,485 --> 00:54:37,972
I think I have to.

918
00:54:38,245 --> 00:54:39,903
I see.

919
00:54:40,135 --> 00:54:41,579
What about you?

920
00:54:41,711 --> 00:54:45,949
Honestly, I think I'll get a headache
from making all these speculations.

921
00:54:45,974 --> 00:54:52,319
When I wasn't interested in you, I didn't
really care about people's identities.

922
00:54:53,831 --> 00:54:56,842
- Same here. I don't care.
- But if I do have to speculate,

923
00:54:56,867 --> 00:54:58,867
you seem like a Money Catcher.

924
00:54:59,472 --> 00:55:02,028
- Oh. He's kind of...
- Money?

925
00:55:03,533 --> 00:55:07,709
(Ji-min thinks Da-Na is a Money Catcher?)

926
00:55:07,920 --> 00:55:13,795
But aside from that, like what I said just
now, the identity doesn't really matter.

927
00:55:14,840 --> 00:55:21,228
It's true that I want to get to know.

928
00:55:22,395 --> 00:55:26,109
But what I'm glad is that
you gave me the chance.

929
00:55:26,535 --> 00:55:32,007
There were some things
that became clear, so I liked it.

930
00:55:32,819 --> 00:55:39,313
I mostly dated my previous boyfriends
because I was drawn to them first.

931
00:55:39,338 --> 00:55:43,508
So I'm not really familiar
with this kind of attention.

932
00:55:43,533 --> 00:55:47,197
- So you dated people you liked first.
- Up until now, yes.

933
00:55:47,557 --> 00:55:49,688
I feel like I'm running away.

934
00:55:50,192 --> 00:55:53,439
If it seems like someone's going
to talk to me, I go the other way.

935
00:55:54,729 --> 00:55:57,129
I don't know how you think about it,

936
00:55:57,601 --> 00:56:01,796
but even talking like this
requires a lot of courage for me.

937
00:56:01,982 --> 00:56:03,824
I don't know how you think, but...

938
00:56:04,278 --> 00:56:05,945
You've avoided me before, haven't you?

939
00:56:05,970 --> 00:56:08,622
- No, I don't think so.
- Oh, really? Okay.

940
00:56:08,647 --> 00:56:09,647
That's good.

941
00:56:10,552 --> 00:56:12,523
I'm curious about
something, but I won't ask.

942
00:56:12,904 --> 00:56:14,938
Why not?

943
00:56:16,227 --> 00:56:18,465
Just. I don't want to.

944
00:56:19,954 --> 00:56:23,564
Just? You don't want to know? You're
curious, but you don't want to know?

945
00:56:24,020 --> 00:56:25,853
Yes, because I could get hurt.

946
00:56:25,878 --> 00:56:27,204
Oh, really?

947
00:56:29,718 --> 00:56:32,162
I think it's, "What do you think about me?"

948
00:56:32,920 --> 00:56:36,428
If she says she doesn't
like him, he might get hurt.

949
00:56:36,453 --> 00:56:38,700
So he doesn't want to hear her answer.

950
00:56:44,535 --> 00:56:46,900
I seem like a fool, right?
I think so, too.

951
00:56:51,188 --> 00:56:56,209
(They just gaze at each other.)

952
00:56:57,948 --> 00:57:00,630
What's this conversation about?
Did they confirm their feelings?

953
00:57:00,655 --> 00:57:03,530
Ji-min said that
he's interested in her,

954
00:57:03,555 --> 00:57:06,919
whether she's a Love
Catcher or a Money Catcher.

955
00:57:06,944 --> 00:57:09,496
The more Da-Na talks, the more
she seems like a Love Catcher.

956
00:57:09,521 --> 00:57:11,402
Same here. I think she's a Love Catcher.

957
00:57:11,427 --> 00:57:13,087
(Unclear)

958
00:57:14,137 --> 00:57:17,233
(The conversation they
only understood ends...)

959
00:57:20,557 --> 00:57:22,311
Why did you guys grow silent?

960
00:57:22,639 --> 00:57:25,218
- The atmosphere isn't good.
- It's so suffocating.

961
00:57:26,904 --> 00:57:29,531
- Oh, what's that?
- All of a sudden?

962
00:57:30,320 --> 00:57:31,487
What's going on?

963
00:57:32,132 --> 00:57:34,425
- Are we checking the lockers?
- No way.

964
00:57:35,523 --> 00:57:37,986
- What's happening?
- What is it?

965
00:57:41,047 --> 00:57:42,411
(Right now...)

966
00:57:42,641 --> 00:57:43,983
"Right now..."

967
00:57:44,591 --> 00:57:47,432
- "Right now..."
- Talk to the one you want?

968
00:57:47,457 --> 00:57:49,593
Oh, what is it? Going on 1:1 dates?

969
00:57:49,618 --> 00:57:52,723
(Right now, you have the
chance to change your identity.)

970
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:56,030
- As expected!
- Right now?

971
00:57:56,055 --> 00:57:57,619
So you can change it!

972
00:58:00,544 --> 00:58:01,861
Why suddenly?

973
00:58:04,445 --> 00:58:05,747
I need to think.

974
00:58:06,289 --> 00:58:07,503
Why now though?

975
00:58:07,551 --> 00:58:10,655
If they're not Money Catchers, but
they're suspected, they might change.

976
00:58:10,680 --> 00:58:13,421
- That's possible. - Wow, it's
confusing. What will they do?

977
00:58:13,960 --> 00:58:16,160
(Before the final selection
day, they have the chance

978
00:58:16,185 --> 00:58:18,385
to change their identity
that will change everything.)

979
00:58:19,470 --> 00:58:22,976
(They have to be more careful than ever.)

980
00:58:25,362 --> 00:58:27,148
They all don't look happy.

981
00:58:27,173 --> 00:58:29,088
(What will they choose?)

982
00:58:32,015 --> 00:58:35,118
Out of those eight people, will
someone change their identity?

983
00:58:35,143 --> 00:58:40,573
(Love or money? What will you choose?)

984
00:58:42,191 --> 00:58:45,194
I hope the one I choose is a Love
Catcher, but I wasn't completely sure.

985
00:58:46,735 --> 00:58:48,560
Should I change my identity or not?

986
00:58:51,186 --> 00:58:54,194
I didn't change, but I
really don't know what she's thinking.

987
00:58:56,326 --> 00:58:58,691
People's feelings are like the wind.

988
00:58:59,241 --> 00:59:01,344
They could be Love Catchers
who become Money Catchers

989
00:59:01,369 --> 00:59:03,195
because they're so frustrated.

990
00:59:03,220 --> 00:59:04,674
There's not enough time.

991
00:59:06,208 --> 00:59:08,074
I really had a lot on my mind.

992
00:59:11,119 --> 00:59:13,186
I actually think I got certain.

993
00:59:15,226 --> 00:59:18,599
He has to be a Love Catcher.
No, wait, even if he isn't...

994
00:59:19,589 --> 00:59:22,731
Oh, I think that means
she's a Love Catcher.

995
00:59:22,756 --> 00:59:26,108
(All 8 participants have
selected their identities.)

996
00:59:26,277 --> 00:59:28,364
(Men's lodging)

997
00:59:29,354 --> 00:59:30,954
We made our choices now.

998
00:59:31,189 --> 00:59:32,589
I had to think a lot.

999
00:59:33,300 --> 00:59:34,500
I have no regrets.

1000
00:59:36,027 --> 00:59:37,439
What do you think Da-Na is?

1001
00:59:37,893 --> 00:59:39,829
I talked with her twice today.

1002
00:59:41,443 --> 00:59:42,991
His eyes are burning.

1003
00:59:43,016 --> 00:59:44,994
She doesn't really seem
like a Money Catcher.

1004
00:59:45,019 --> 00:59:48,750
My heart says she's a Love Catcher, but...

1005
00:59:48,775 --> 00:59:50,564
my mind thinks otherwise.

1006
00:59:51,701 --> 00:59:52,768
That's possible.

1007
00:59:52,989 --> 00:59:56,599
We don't know anything.
They're nothing but speculations.

1008
00:59:56,917 --> 00:59:57,917
I have no regrets.

1009
00:59:59,049 --> 01:00:00,763
(Complicated)

1010
01:00:00,981 --> 01:00:03,124
Is the prize money $50,000 or $100,000?

1011
01:00:03,149 --> 01:00:04,237
Did he change to love?

1012
01:00:04,262 --> 01:00:06,795
Seriously? Why is he bringing that up?

1013
01:00:07,631 --> 01:00:09,194
Is the prize money $50,000 or $100,000?

1014
01:00:10,397 --> 01:00:13,704
(At his words, their gazes
grow uncomfortable.)

1015
01:00:17,010 --> 01:00:19,376
(A night of irreversible choices deepens)

1016
01:00:19,408 --> 01:00:21,713
(Women's lodging)

1017
01:00:24,022 --> 01:00:25,347
You weren't able to talk it out?

1018
01:00:27,367 --> 01:00:29,549
About whether he's Love or Money...

1019
01:00:34,295 --> 01:00:36,128
- I really don't know.
- That's not important?

1020
01:00:36,153 --> 01:00:37,153
I just...

1021
01:00:40,157 --> 01:00:42,593
I wonder how many people
changed their identities.

1022
01:00:45,981 --> 01:00:48,552
- Wow, but I really have no idea.
- Same here.

1023
01:00:49,608 --> 01:00:55,411
(Today's Question: How many
people changed their identities?)

1024
01:00:56,171 --> 01:00:57,885
The number of people who changed.

1025
01:00:59,031 --> 01:01:01,483
That's why these cards were here.

1026
01:01:01,508 --> 01:01:05,242
Honestly, I was trying to
figure out who went through

1027
01:01:05,267 --> 01:01:08,586
something major enough
to change their identity.

1028
01:01:08,685 --> 01:01:14,017
I think it's Da-Na and one of the guys.

1029
01:01:15,860 --> 01:01:19,534
I think Yeo-min, who just
gave up, changed her identity.

1030
01:01:19,559 --> 01:01:21,687
- One vote to her.
- Yeah.

1031
01:01:22,438 --> 01:01:26,366
I simply thought who would
go from Love to Money.

1032
01:01:26,391 --> 01:01:31,291
In order to change to a Money Catcher, you
have to be sure that someone's into you.

1033
01:01:31,319 --> 01:01:34,025
But the obvious one is Da-Na.

1034
01:01:34,050 --> 01:01:37,266
Probability-wise, at least one
of them probably chose her.

1035
01:01:37,707 --> 01:01:40,756
I also think it's Ha-neul and Su-won.

1036
01:01:41,256 --> 01:01:44,720
They were both Love Catchers, but
things didn't work out, so they changed

1037
01:01:44,745 --> 01:01:47,880
to Money Catchers, and at the
end, they'll kind of go like, "What?"

1038
01:01:49,278 --> 01:01:52,674
I think three people
changed their identities.

1039
01:01:53,338 --> 01:01:56,706
I feel like Ji-min went
from Money to Love, and

1040
01:01:56,731 --> 01:01:59,959
he'll now go straight
for the person he likes.

1041
01:01:59,984 --> 01:02:02,495
And who is that person? Da-Na or Ha-neul?

1042
01:02:02,520 --> 01:02:05,284
If he changes to a Love
Catcher, it'll probably be Ha-neul.

1043
01:02:05,962 --> 01:02:08,245
- So I'll go with one person.
- One person.

1044
01:02:08,894 --> 01:02:11,801
I think Jae-hyung is a really cool person.

1045
01:02:11,826 --> 01:02:17,268
So I think he's a Money Catcher who
will change to a Love Catcher because of

1046
01:02:17,293 --> 01:02:22,592
his feelings for Da-Na and let her
know that's how serious he is about her.

1047
01:02:22,617 --> 01:02:28,132
If you think about it, Ji-min was
just careful about his feelings.

1048
01:02:28,157 --> 01:02:31,563
He talked with a lot of
people, but he got interested in

1049
01:02:31,588 --> 01:02:35,291
Da-Na and connected with her,
so he changed to a Love Catcher.

1050
01:02:36,726 --> 01:02:39,233
And I think Yeo-min changed, too.

1051
01:02:39,480 --> 01:02:45,054
Since it's so obvious that
Won-jae has feelings for Da-Na,

1052
01:02:45,079 --> 01:02:47,964
she changed her identity since
she came across the opportunity.

1053
01:02:47,989 --> 01:02:50,316
So including her, there are three people.

1054
01:02:52,067 --> 01:02:55,019
- The winner today will get two coins.
- For real?

1055
01:02:55,044 --> 01:02:57,657
Ho-jun and I are both
in first place right now.

1056
01:02:57,898 --> 01:03:00,270
We only have one coin each.

1057
01:03:00,295 --> 01:03:03,091
Whoever gets it right today
will go straight to first place.

1058
01:03:03,116 --> 01:03:05,078
- Then I'll change my answer.
- Seriously?

1059
01:03:05,986 --> 01:03:08,668
- I'll go with four people.
- Really?

1060
01:03:09,077 --> 01:03:11,592
So you're saying we can't both be winners?

1061
01:03:11,617 --> 01:03:13,365
Of course not. I need
to be the sole winner.

1062
01:03:13,390 --> 01:03:16,664
- It'd be funny if no one changed.
- That's possible.

1063
01:03:16,689 --> 01:03:18,577
- Huh?
- Will you change your answer?

1064
01:03:18,602 --> 01:03:23,198
- I feel like it's zero.
- Your zipper says zero.

1065
01:03:25,159 --> 01:03:26,838
(Foresightedness?)

1066
01:03:26,990 --> 01:03:28,689
Your earrings look like zeroes, too.

1067
01:03:28,714 --> 01:03:30,977
- I believe in things like this.
- Will you change?

1068
01:03:31,217 --> 01:03:34,130
- I'll go with zero.
- For real?

1069
01:03:34,702 --> 01:03:35,702
Awesome.

1070
01:03:37,507 --> 01:03:41,519
(The number of people
who changed their identities:)

1071
01:03:43,227 --> 01:03:45,693
(The choice that will most
greatly affect the final decision)

1072
01:03:45,718 --> 01:03:47,702
(How many... are there?)

1073
01:03:50,192 --> 01:03:51,406
(2 people?)

1074
01:03:52,939 --> 01:03:54,194
(1 person?)

1075
01:03:56,387 --> 01:03:57,673
(Is it really zero?)

1076
01:03:59,136 --> 01:04:00,874
I thought it was zero for a second!

1077
01:04:02,587 --> 01:04:03,902
(Is it really 4?)

1078
01:04:06,970 --> 01:04:08,175
(Really?)

1079
01:04:10,359 --> 01:04:11,608
(Oh? 2 people?)

1080
01:04:14,724 --> 01:04:16,263
What are you doing?

1081
01:04:16,288 --> 01:04:17,860
(It can't be.)

1082
01:04:21,739 --> 01:04:22,739
0 people!

1083
01:04:23,822 --> 01:04:24,889
Are you serious?

1084
01:04:24,914 --> 01:04:26,236
(No way!)

1085
01:04:26,261 --> 01:04:27,578
(A rapper's hunch)

1086
01:04:27,603 --> 01:04:31,493
- Really? - I thought it was
strange that this was here!

1087
01:04:32,092 --> 01:04:35,631
This was all fruitless!
We all made deductions,

1088
01:04:36,769 --> 01:04:39,047
but Loco just chose
zero 'cause of his zipper!

1089
01:04:39,413 --> 01:04:41,592
Give the honors to your stylist.

1090
01:04:42,267 --> 01:04:43,594
(Thanks!)

1091
01:04:45,504 --> 01:04:46,670
No one changed?

1092
01:04:50,209 --> 01:04:53,399
(However, the last night at
the Love Mansion isn't over yet.)

1093
01:04:54,192 --> 01:04:56,957
(Late at night, the screen turns on again.)

1094
01:04:57,777 --> 01:04:59,285
Why am I getting so nervous?

1095
01:05:03,109 --> 01:05:04,109
What is it now?

1096
01:05:08,876 --> 01:05:11,138
(Final Selection)

1097
01:05:11,610 --> 01:05:13,824
- They're already deciding now?
- Right now? Why?

1098
01:05:13,849 --> 01:05:15,128
There's one day left.

1099
01:05:15,153 --> 01:05:16,876
- Isn't there?
- We're choosing today?

1100
01:05:17,958 --> 01:05:18,958
Right now?

1101
01:05:19,285 --> 01:05:20,352
What's going on?

1102
01:05:20,753 --> 01:05:21,753
What?

1103
01:05:22,096 --> 01:05:24,096
- It's too late.
- Right now?

1104
01:05:29,502 --> 01:05:33,795
(You will go on a final date before
you make your final selection.)

1105
01:05:34,414 --> 01:05:36,675
(From now on, you can
date whoever you want, go

1106
01:05:36,700 --> 01:05:38,866
wherever you want, and
do whatever you want.,)

1107
01:05:38,891 --> 01:05:42,847
(24 hours later, you will
make your final selection.)

1108
01:05:45,767 --> 01:05:48,306
They're dating for 24 hours?

1109
01:05:48,912 --> 01:05:50,809
They're totally free to do what they want.

1110
01:05:50,834 --> 01:05:53,234
- That's a shocking offer.
- It is.

1111
01:05:53,758 --> 01:05:54,758
What?

1112
01:05:55,004 --> 01:05:57,401
- We don't have to sleep?
- Oh my god!

1113
01:05:58,288 --> 01:06:00,088
So we have total freedom for 24 hours?

1114
01:06:00,623 --> 01:06:02,924
For real? Just like this?

1115
01:06:03,363 --> 01:06:04,537
Wow, what is this?

1116
01:06:05,278 --> 01:06:06,944
This is really like a fight.

1117
01:06:07,685 --> 01:06:09,812
- It's going to be crazy.
- This is hard.

1118
01:06:10,998 --> 01:06:12,911
I haven't felt this in a while.

1119
01:06:14,169 --> 01:06:15,447
Isn't this a war?

1120
01:06:17,330 --> 01:06:20,195
(The doorbell suddenly rings?)

1121
01:06:20,651 --> 01:06:21,784
We should go out.

1122
01:06:25,990 --> 01:06:27,433
(No one's here though.)

1123
01:06:28,005 --> 01:06:29,005
What was that?

1124
01:06:29,606 --> 01:06:32,058
- Hang on. There are cell phones.
- Phones.

1125
01:06:32,750 --> 01:06:34,560
- I guess we're getting texts.
- Cell phones?

1126
01:06:37,049 --> 01:06:39,081
(The doorbell rings here, too.)

1127
01:06:39,106 --> 01:06:40,106
Who is it?

1128
01:06:40,902 --> 01:06:42,035
Should we go out?

1129
01:06:46,068 --> 01:06:47,949
- What's going on?
- Oh my god!

1130
01:06:48,307 --> 01:06:50,419
- Why are they giving us this?
- Oh my gosh.

1131
01:06:51,093 --> 01:06:52,693
We can use this outside?

1132
01:06:53,750 --> 01:06:56,313
What if I end up staying here alone again?

1133
01:06:56,968 --> 01:06:58,412
This has never happened before.

1134
01:06:59,240 --> 01:07:00,867
This is shocking!

1135
01:07:02,725 --> 01:07:04,958
(In the middle of
confusion, they all get a text.)

1136
01:07:04,983 --> 01:07:07,055
"Ask the person you like on a date."

1137
01:07:07,080 --> 01:07:10,147
"You can use your phone
or ask them directly face to face."

1138
01:07:12,405 --> 01:07:13,747
God, hang on.

1139
01:07:14,930 --> 01:07:16,343
Why am I getting so nervous?

1140
01:07:18,118 --> 01:07:20,855
He says that, but he's
slowly getting ready to go out.

1141
01:07:21,165 --> 01:07:23,350
He's preparing to go out faster than them.

1142
01:07:23,375 --> 01:07:24,836
(As expected of Ji-min.)

1143
01:07:25,523 --> 01:07:30,983
(The 24 hours has begun,
but only silence fills that time.)

1144
01:07:37,694 --> 01:07:38,892
- Is he going?
- He's going.

1145
01:07:38,917 --> 01:07:41,171
I don't bother with texts.
I'm going there right away.

1146
01:07:41,782 --> 01:07:42,782
Nice!

1147
01:07:43,138 --> 01:07:44,672
Our Su-won has changed.

1148
01:07:44,847 --> 01:07:47,275
I don't bother with texts.
I'm going there right away.

1149
01:07:48,287 --> 01:07:50,221
Su-won is the fastest to act.

1150
01:07:52,228 --> 01:07:53,656
Aren't you taking your phone?

1151
01:07:54,267 --> 01:07:55,800
(Going straightforward)

1152
01:07:56,537 --> 01:08:00,812
(Right now, Su-won needs a
way for his sincerity to reach her.)

1153
01:08:02,113 --> 01:08:05,810
(Like always, Su-won
approaches Ha-neul first.)

1154
01:08:08,093 --> 01:08:12,737
(During the last date before the final
selection, will he have a good time?)

1155
01:08:14,442 --> 01:08:16,847
- That's the end?
- I'm so curious though.

1156
01:08:16,872 --> 01:08:19,230
What happens now?
Will they go far, far away?

1157
01:08:19,255 --> 01:08:21,382
- Wow, but I'm totally clueless.
- Same.

1158
01:08:23,657 --> 01:08:26,204
Ha-neul, wanna go on a date with me?

1159
01:08:27,591 --> 01:08:29,551
Have you ever had a
long-distance relationship?

1160
01:08:29,576 --> 01:08:31,241
I tried it, and it's manageable.

1161
01:08:33,167 --> 01:08:34,422
Are you not upset anymore?

1162
01:08:35,075 --> 01:08:36,797
Do you feel better now?

1163
01:08:38,428 --> 01:08:39,828
Are you in your room?

1164
01:08:41,819 --> 01:08:43,287
Can we talk for a moment?

1165
01:08:45,356 --> 01:08:47,245
Hello? Where are you?

1166
01:08:48,549 --> 01:08:49,816
Who here got texts?

1167
01:08:50,440 --> 01:08:52,322
- From who?
- Won-jae.

1168
01:08:52,681 --> 01:08:54,736
You look like you have a lot on your mind.

1169
01:08:55,557 --> 01:08:57,811
I really can't do this.

1170
01:08:59,354 --> 01:09:00,989
There's nothing I can do.

1171
01:09:02,549 --> 01:09:04,082
We were given 24 hours.

1172
01:09:04,533 --> 01:09:08,838
If it's okay with you, I want to
spend the entire time with you.

1173
01:09:11,050 --> 01:09:12,359
You're really pretty.

1174
01:09:15,856 --> 01:09:18,698
I couldn't sleep because I
wanted to go on a date with you.

1175
01:09:19,383 --> 01:09:21,114
This feels really strange.

1176
01:09:22,306 --> 01:09:24,775
If you reject me, it's over.
